ww.engadget.com/the-best-of-ces-2024-220054009.html">在活动中公布的最佳设备</a>清单，并且成为了人们经常谈论的话题。厨房小工具必须非常特别，才能与最新的笔记本电脑、智能电视和<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/rabbit-r1-is-an-adorable-ai-powered-assistant-co-designed-by-teenage-engineering-001051537.html">兔子形状的拟人人工智能助手竞争，从而引起轰动。</a>换句话说，GE 的 Profile Smart 室内吸烟器可以满足您的需求。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p><core-commerce id="c2a3400b053241a1b077745e4327d36a" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p>我们赞扬该设备为家庭厨师提供了一种在室内熏制肉类的合法方式，而这对于以前的公寓居民等来说是遥不可及的。 GE 的设备放弃了电加热元件的明火，将低烟度和缓慢的烟雾带入室内。</p><p>我们还喜欢内置的过滤系统，可以防止臭味烟雾飘散到整个家中。至于高科技组件，这款吸烟者连接到 Wi-Fi 进行远程烹饪和监控，这是我们在<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ge-profile-smart-indoor-smoker-150044423.html">官方实际操作中赞赏的功能。</a>我们拿到了单位准备的牛胸肉<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/we-tried-meat-from-the-ge-profile-smart-indoor-smoker-and-it-was-delicious-130029336.html">，确实很美味。</a></p><p>该设备的主要缺点是价格。在吸烟者身上花费 1,000 美元可能会清空银行账户并加快离婚程序。 700 美元的折扣使其成为更合理的购买选择。我们很快就会发布对吸烟者的官方评论。</p><p><em>在 Twitter 上</em><em>关注</em><a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://twitter.com/EngadgetDeals"><em>@EngadgetDeals</em></a>并<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://subscription.yahoo.net/Newsletter/Preference/sub?b=engadgetdeals&amp;src"><em>订阅 Engadget Deals 时事通讯，</em></a><em>了解最新的科技交易和购买建议。</em></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/the-new-ge-profile-smart-indoor-smoker-is-300-off-right-now-173049256.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-new-ge-profile-smart-indoor-smoker-is-300-off-right-now-173049256.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 55741adf-8987-4122-8b3d-b12e988c429f</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Lawrence Bonk]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 24 Jan 2024 17:30:49 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1706117505</ingested><modified> 2024-01-24T17:31:49+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Personal Finance - Lifestyle]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="935" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F89003380-badb-11ee-bb5f-af2ac0fb70b8&amp;resize=1400%2C935&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=cc06b3b0334ae227c1ac4d122ad13d2adea45b8d" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="935" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F89003380-badb-11ee-bb5f-af2ac0fb70b8&amp;resize=1400%2C935&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=7e1fc689fe89f71d201ade0ac739be281ddfbca2" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[GE]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A man enjoying some smoked meat as the smoker sits beside him.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[GE Profile Indoor Smoker]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[All the big tech layoffs of 2023 and 2024]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>科技行业一直受到经济不景气、新冠肺炎 (COVID-19) 大流行和一些明显的商业失误的影响。虽然这导致了 2022 年的裁员，但不幸的是，裁员人数在 2023 年有所增加，而且到目前为止，2024 年似乎还在加速。跟踪这些举措可能很困难，因此我们汇总了 2023 年的所有重大裁员情况。一个地方，并将随着情况的发展继续更新这个故事。</p><h2> 2024 年 1 月</h2><h3>Duolingo 裁员</h3><p><a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/duolingo-lays-off-contractors-as-it-starts-relying-more-on-ai-060331602.html">Duolingo 裁减了 10% 的承包商</a>，并表示它能够使用生成式 AI 来完成人类员工过去执行的一些任务。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h3>统一裁员</h3><p><a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/unity-is-cutting-a-quarter-of-its-workforce-074331467.html">Unity 解雇了 1,800 人</a>，占员工总数的四分之一。除此之外，该公司过去两年还裁员 1,110 多人。</p><h3>人性化的人工智能裁员</h3><p>Humane 甚至在其旗舰产品<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/humane-ai-pin-orders-will-start-shipping-in-march-185449334.html">Ai pin</a>上市之前<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/humane-lays-off-staff-before-its-ai-pin-begins-shipping-103548514.html">就裁掉了 4% 的员工</a>。</p><h3>抽搐裁员</h3><p><a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitch-is-reportedly-laying-off-35-percent-of-its-workforce-085946333.html">亚马逊旗下的 Twitch 正在裁员 35%，即 500 多人，这一数字</a>令人震惊。首席执行官丹·克兰西（Dan Clancy）在给员工的一封信中表示，“我们的组织仍然远远超出了我们业务规模所需的规模。”</p><h3>亚马逊裁员</h3><p>就在亚马逊旗下 Twitch 确认将裁员 500 名员工的同一天， <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://variety.com/2024/streaming/news/amazon-lay-offs-prime-video-mgm-studios-1235867454/"><em>Variety</em></a>报道称，亚马逊本身也将在 Prime Video 和米高梅影城裁员“数百人”。 1 月底，亚马逊<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazons-latest-layoffs-hit-buy-with-prime-which-lets-you-use-prime-benefits-on-other-websites-212140862.html">还削减了 Buy with Prime 计划背后 5% 的员工</a>。</p><h3>元裁员</h3><p>Meta 的裁员计划将持续到 2024 年。 <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-reportedly-laid-off-60-technical-program-managers-at-instagram-095558424.html">据报道，该公司已经解雇了 Instagram 的 60 名技术项目经理</a>。</p><h3>谷歌裁员</h3><p><a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-lays-off-hundreds-of-employees-in-its-assistant-hardware-and-other-divisions-082540416.html">据报道，在另一轮紧缩开支中，谷歌解雇了助理和硬件部门等部门的数百名员工</a>。据称，除了裁员之外，谷歌还重组了 Pixel、Nest 和 Fitbit 部门，这导致 Fitbit 的联合创始人离开了公司。几天后，谷歌<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-is-laying-off-hundreds-of-workers-who-sell-ads-to-big-businesses-190057680.html">解雇了广告业务的数百名员工</a>。首席执行官桑达尔·皮查伊后来<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-ceo-says-more-layoffs-expected-throughout-the-year-in-internal-memo-044016588.html">在一份内部备忘录中表示</a>，全年将进行更多裁员，而母公司 Alphabet 则从其 X 登月实验室<a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/alphabet-is-cutting-dozens-of-jobs-at-its-x-moonshot-lab-203505073.html">削减了数十个工作岗位</a>。</p><h3>不和谐裁员</h3><p><a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/discord-lays-off-170-workers-in-latest-round-of-cuts-211541127.html">据报道，Discord 已解雇 170 名员工</a>，占其员工总数的 17%。在<a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/11/24034705/discord-layoffs-17-percent-employees">The Verge 首次报道的</a>一份备忘录中，首席执行官 Jason Citron 表示，该公司在 2020 年雇佣了太多员工。</p><h3>防暴游戏裁员</h3><p>继 2023 年游戏行业<a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2023-was-a-year-of-layoffs-and-acquisitions-this-weeks-gaming-news-163028348.html">陷入危机</a>后，Riot Games 宣布在全球范围内<a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/riot-games-is-laying-off-11-percent-of-its-workforce-globally-022034243.html">裁员 11%</a> ，影响 530 人。</p><h3>易趣裁员</h3><p>电子商务巨头 eBay 正在裁员<a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ebay-is-laying-off-9-percent-of-its-workforce-035136287.html">约 1,000 名员工</a>，约占其全职员工的 9%。该公司还计划在未来几个月内缩减承包商数量。</p><h3> TikTok 裁员</h3><p>TikTok <a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tiktok-is-reportedly-laying-off-workers-to-cut-costs-073546895.html">证实解雇了 60 名员工</a>，其中大部分在销售和广告部门。</p><h2> 2023 年 12 月</h2><h2></h2><p><strong>Spotify 裁员</strong></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-laying-off-17-percent-of-employees-across-the-company-081521784.html">Spotify 首席执行官丹尼尔·埃克 (Daniel Ek) 在节前新闻稿中宣布，Spotify 将裁员 17%</a> 。</p><p><strong>新世界互动</strong></p><p>《Insurgency》系列和《Day of Infamy》的开发商在 12 月<a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/multiple-game-developers-announce-layoffs-including-ea-owned-codemasters-183318247.html">解雇了</a>员工，具体人数不详。</p><p><strong>小建</strong></p><p>独立游戏开发商 Tinybuild 也以成本重组为由裁员，具体人数不详。</p><p><strong>代码大师</strong></p><p>EA 旗下的工作室于 12 月裁员。在这里，也不清楚有多少员工失业。</p><p><strong>潮汐</strong></p><p>这家音乐流媒体<a data-i13n="cpos:21;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tidal-is-laying-off-10-percent-of-its-staff-140112305.html">公司于 12 月宣布将裁员 10%</a> 。此前，母公司 Block Inc. 在 11 月宣布将员工人数限制在 12,000 人。</p><p><strong>埃特西</strong></p><p>Etsy <a data-i13n="cpos:22;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/etsy-is-laying-off-11-percent-of-its-staff-201545615.html">将裁员</a>11%，即约 225 名员工。该公司还对其高管进行了改组，两名高管将于 2024 年初离职。</p><h2> 2023 年 11 月</h2><h2></h2><p><strong>育碧蒙特利尔裁员</strong></p><p>11 月初，育碧在蒙特利尔办事处<a data-i13n="cpos:23;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ubisoft-montreal-lays-off-98-people-as-part-of-a-corporate-restructuring-effort-195616771.html">解雇了 98 名员工</a>，该办事处被认为是该公司最大的内部开发团队的所在地。大多数失业者从事的是工商管理和 IT 行业。总体而言，该公司在最新的季度收益报告中表示，过去12个月已裁员约1,000人，包括裁员和不替换自愿离职的员工。</p><p><strong>邮轮裁员</strong></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:24;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/cruise-is-reportedly-planning-to-lay-off-employees-after-weeks-of-crises-195546324.html">据报道，通用汽车旗下无人驾驶汽车子公司 Cruise 在 11 月份告诉员工</a>，计划解雇部分员工。就在同一周，通用汽车因行人碰撞事故<a data-i13n="cpos:25;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/gm-recalls-nearly-1000-cruise-robotaxis-after-pedestrian-collision-183049933.html">召回了</a>Cruise 的整个 950 辆机器人出租车车队。 <a data-i13n="cpos:26;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/cruise-lays-off-24-percent-of-its-workforce-164800680.html">Cruise 去年 12 月证实</a>，裁员将包括约 900 名员工，占员工总数的 24%。</p><p><strong>快速裁员</strong></p><p>Snap <a data-i13n="cpos:27;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/snap-lays-off-20-product-managers-to-speed-up-decision-making-071010069.html">解雇了 20 名产品经理</a>，声称此举将加快决策速度。</p><p><strong>亚马逊裁员</strong></p><p>据<em>路透社</em>和<em>彭博社</em>等多家知名新闻媒体报道，亚马逊<a data-i13n="cpos:28;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-cuts-180-jobs-from-its-gaming-division-204231214.html">从其游戏部门裁员 180 人</a>。此次裁员包括亚马逊支持的 Twitch 频道 Crown 的全体员工。另外，11 月晚些时候，亚马逊<a data-i13n="cpos:29;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-is-laying-off-several-hundred-employees-working-on-alexa-190339189.html">解雇了数百名 Alexa 员工</a>。在人工智能方面，人们普遍认为该公司落后于 ChatGPT 母公司 OpenAI 等竞争对手。</p><p><strong>字节跳动裁员</strong></p><p>据报道，TikTok 的母公司字节跳动已<a data-i13n="cpos:30;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/bytedances-latest-layoffs-have-reportedly-gutted-the-publisher-of-marvel-snap-101548665.html">裁减其游戏部门的数百个职位</a>。据说它在 2017 年收购的出版商 Nuverse 在此过程中遭受了损失。</p><p><strong>统一裁员</strong></p><p>作为公司“重组”的一部分， <a data-i13n="cpos:31;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/unity-cuts-265-jobs-as-part-of-a-company-reset-123511764.html">Unity Software 裁员 265 人</a>，占员工总数的 3.8%。</p><h2></h2><h2> 2023 年 10 月</h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/0307b0d0-6c3b-11ee-abe7-7b5caed0f041" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/0307b0d0-6c3b-11ee-abe7-7b5caed0f041" style="height:2000px;width:3000px;" alt="文件 - 在 2016 年 9 月 22 日星期四的文件照片中，LinkedIn 徽标在旧金山的产品发布会上显示。 2017 年 8 月 14 日星期一，联邦法官命令 LinkedIn 停止阻止初创公司 hiQ Labs, Inc. 抓取 LinkedIn 个人资料中的数据。 （美联社照片/埃里克·里斯伯格，档案）" data-uuid="4127eff7-1fac-330d-ba73-d39211a72448"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">美联社</div></figure><p><strong>领英裁员</strong></p><p>LinkedIn 表示，在今年的第二轮裁员中，该公司将<a data-i13n="cpos:32;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/linkedin-lays-off-600-workers-in-second-round-of-cuts-this-year-154223614.html">裁掉来自工程、产品、人才和财务团队的约 668 名员工</a>。 5 月，LinkedIn 表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:33;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/linkedin-is-laying-off-716-staff-and-closing-its-job-search-app-in-china-141636741.html">裁员 716 人</a>，并关闭其在中国的求职应用程序。在两轮裁员之间，LinkedIn 将在 2023 年裁员近 1,400 人。</p><p></p><h2> 2023 年 9 月</h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/e6f110f0-4d98-11ee-bcdd-7d03544e5041" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-08/e6f110f0-4d98-11ee-bcdd-7d03544e5041" style="height:2240px;width:3360px;" alt="文件 - 这张 2020 年 8 月 13 日的文件照片显示了俄勒冈州波特兰遥控器上的 Roku 徽标。Roku 正在裁员约 10%，即 360 人，因为这家流媒体公司希望降低开支。 Roku Inc. 在 2023 年 9 月 6 日星期三提交的监管文件中表示，预计与裁员相关的重组费用为 4500 万至 6500 万美元（美联社照片/Jenny Kane）" data-uuid="67977cd9-ab44-317b-8f44-c4831b60fcc8"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">美联社</div></figure><h3>Epic Games 裁员</h3><p>Epic Games <a data-i13n="cpos:34;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/epic-games-is-laying-off-16-percent-of-its-workforce-and-selling-bandcamp-211830580.html">解雇了 16%</a>的员工，即约 830 名员工。首席执行官蒂姆·斯威尼(Tim Sweeney)<a data-i13n="cpos:35;pos:1" href="https://www.epicgames.com/site/en-US/news/layoffs-at-epic">在一封致员工的公开信中</a>表示，公司花的钱比赚的钱“多得多”，“我们的结论是裁员是唯一的办法”。此前，该公司曾试图通过冻结招聘和削减营销支出来降低成本。</p><h3></h3><h3> Roku裁员</h3><p>Roku <a data-i13n="cpos:36;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/roku-lays-off-300-workers-and-removes-streaming-content-to-save-money-183715207.html">2023 年第二轮裁员</a>将导致另外 300 名员工离开公司，除了<a data-i13n="cpos:37;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/roku-will-lay-off-another-200-workers-132908304.html">3 月份解雇的</a>200 名员工以及 2022 年末<a data-i13n="cpos:38;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/roku-layoffs-streaming-2022-201541882.html">解雇的</a>另外 200 名员工之外。Roku 再次寻求降低成本，并在减少员工人数的同时，它正试图通过从其平台上删除节目和电影、整合办公空间并减少外部服务支出来做到这一点。</p><h2> 2023 年 7 月</h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/c4754d20-1684-11ee-9fb7-bed70f25a024" style="height:3453px;width:5341px;" alt="法国巴黎 - 6 月 14 日：Google 徽标于 2023 年 6 月 14 日在法国巴黎凡尔赛门展览中心举行的 Viva Technology 会议期间显示。 Viva Technology 是欧洲最大的科技展，但也采用独特的数字格式，由于创新而重新连接和重新启动，为期 4 天。该活动汇集了初创公司、首席执行官、投资者、技术领导者以及所有正在塑造互联网未来的数字化转型参与者。该年度技术大会又称为 VivaTech，由阳狮集团 (Publicis Groupe) 和 Groupe Les Echos 于 2016 年创办，致力于促进创新和创业。 （切斯诺特/盖蒂图片社拍摄）" data-uuid="1fa0e99f-c7e5-359f-b12c-c8d8313a01f0"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">切斯诺/盖蒂图片社</div></figure><h3>谷歌裁员</h3><p>谷歌在 7 月份引起了人们的关注，当时其合同合作伙伴埃森哲<a data-i13n="cpos:39;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-lays-off-contractors-who-unionized-last-month-193020753.html">解雇了</a>80 名帮助分包商，这些分包商在前一个月投票成立了 Alphabet 工人联盟 (CWA)。埃森哲将此举归因于削减成本。尽管该公司表示尊重分包商加入工会的权利，但前团队指责谷歌对劳工组织者进行报复。</p><h3> CD Projekt Red 裁员</h3><p><em>《赛博朋克 2077》</em>的创作者也未能幸免于商业挑战。 CD Projekt Red 在 7 月份警告称，它将在未来几个月内裁员<a data-i13n="cpos:40;pos:1" href="https://www.cdprojekt.com/en/media/news/cd-projekt-red-organizational-update/">约 100 人</a>，约占员工总数的 9%。员工最晚将在 2024 年第一季度被解雇。首席执行官 Adam Kiciński 坦白了原因：CDPR 因重组而“人满为患”，旨在更好地处理游戏开发商不断扩大的产品路线图，其中包括新的《赛博朋克》和《巫师》游戏。</p><h2> 2023 年 6 月</h2><h2></h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-02/25293fe0-8f87-11ec-adda-f9ec1ab41fca" alt="在这张摄于 2022 年 2 月 11 日的插图中，可以在显示的 Spotify 徽标前看到小雕像。REUTERS/Dado Ruvic/Ilustration" data-uuid="b7eaecfc-c76c-3536-95b2-d97f7b8007fd"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">达多·鲁维奇/路透社</div></figure><h3>Spotify 裁员</h3><p>Spotify 继 1 月份的裁员计划之后，于 6 月份宣布将在其播客部门<a data-i13n="cpos:41;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-is-laying-off-200-employees-from-its-podcast-division-134749721.html">裁员 200 人</a>。此举是更有针对性的方法的一部分，旨在为创作者和节目提供优化的资源来培育播客。该公司还将其 Gimlet 和 Parcast 制作团队合并为新的 Spotify Studios 部门。</p><h3> GrubHub 裁员</h3><p>GrubHub 面临着来自经济和 Uber 等竞争对手的巨大压力，这导致其在 6 月份<a data-i13n="cpos:42;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/grubhub-lays-off-15-percent-of-its-employees-190005627.html">解雇了 15% 的员工</a>，即大约 400 名员工。就在几周前，即将卸任的首席执行官亚当·德威特 (Adam DeWitt) 正式离开食品配送服务行业。新任首席执行官霍华德·米格达尔 (Howard Migdal) 声称，裁员将有助于公司保持“竞争力”。</p><h3>拥抱集团裁员</h3><p>游戏发行巨头 Embracer Group 于 6 月<a data-i13n="cpos:43;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/embracer-announces-layoffs-and-game-cancellations-after-a-2-billion-deal-falls-through-144311854.html">宣布了裁员计划</a>，作为旨在削减成本的重大重组工作的一部分。该公司没有透露 17,000 名员工中有多少人会受到影响，但预计检修将持续到 3 月份。消息传出后不久，Embracer 透露，尽管有口头协议，但该公司还是失去了与一位未透露姓名的合作伙伴的 20 亿美元交易。</p><h3>索诺斯裁员</h3><p>Sonos 最近一直在努力扭亏为盈，并且正在削减成本以重回正轨。该公司 6 月份表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:44;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sonos-lays-off-7-percent-of-its-workforce-161529844.html">裁员 7%</a> ，即大约 130 个工作岗位。它还计划出售房地产并重新考虑项目支出。首席执行官帕特里克·斯宾塞表示，“持续的不利因素”包括销售萎缩。</p><h3>普莱克斯裁员</h3><p>Plex 可能是许多用户流媒体本地和在线媒体的首选应用程序，但这并没有帮助它的命运。该公司 6 月份解雇了<a data-i13n="cpos:45;pos:1" href="https://techcrunch.com/2023/06/29/plex-layoffs-advertising-slowdown/?guccounter=1">大约 20% 的员工</a>，即 37 人。削减影响到所有领域。据报道，Plex 感受到了广告市场放缓的打击，并渴望削减成本并扭亏为盈。</p><h2> 2023年5月</h2><h2></h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-images/2020-07/0137d510-bd24-11ea-bd56-cc42949aa7b4" alt="2018 年 10 月 22 日，一名员工在加拿大安大略省渥太华的 Shopify 总部工作。REUTERS/Chris Wattie" data-uuid="c94e28de-1bab-3636-9170-a3052663b263"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">路透社/克里斯·瓦蒂</div></figure><h2></h2><h3>Shopify裁员</h3><p>Shopify 的电子商务平台在疫情最严重的时候发挥了重要作用，但这家加拿大公司现在正在缩减规模，因为疫情高峰已经结束。 5 月份，该公司解雇了<a data-i13n="cpos:46;pos:1" href="https://news.shopify.com/important-team-and-business-changes">20% 的员工</a>，并将其物流业务出售给 Flexport。创始人 Tobi Lütke 表示，裁员是为了“全神贯注”Shopify 的核心使命所必需的，并承认既然“稳定的经济繁荣时期”已经结束，公司需要提高效率。</p><h3>北极星裁员</h3><p>Polestar 在 5 月份推迟了其首款电动 SUV（Polestar 3）的生产，这对其员工造成了影响。沃尔沃衍生品牌 5 月份表示，由于面临制造预期下降和经济不景气的情况，将<a data-i13n="cpos:47;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-polestar-3-and-volvo-ex90-are-both-delayed-until-2024-210052700.html">裁员 10%</a>以降低成本。 Polestar 表示，沃尔沃需要更多时间进行软件开发和测试，这也导致了 EX90 的推迟。</p><h3> SoundCloud 裁员</h3><p>SoundCloud 继去年大规模裁员后，今年 5 月又进行了更多裁员。这家流媒体音频服务公司表示，为了在 2023 年实现盈利，它将<a data-i13n="cpos:48;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/soundcloud-will-lay-off-eight-percent-of-its-staff-in-hopes-of-becoming-profitable-204510023.html">裁员 8%</a> <em>。Billboard</em>消息人士称，该公司希望在今年第四季度实现盈利。</p><h2> 2023 年 4 月</h2><h2></h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-07/63baa330-085d-11ed-bf69-3a111366367f" alt="Lyft 徽标可见于 2022 年 6 月 27 日拍摄的这张插图中。REUTERS/Dado Ruvic/Illustration" data-uuid="e196f6c1-e49f-3cf7-b77a-ffed6ca4eb68"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">达多·鲁维奇/路透社</div></figure><h3>Lyft 裁员</h3><p>Lyft 于 2022 年 11 月解雇了 13% 的员工，但在 4 月份采取了进一步措施。这家拼车公司表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:49;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/lyft-is-laying-off-26-percent-of-employees-172550913.html">裁员 1,072 名员工</a>，约占其员工总数的 26%。就在几周前，亚马逊前高管大卫·瑞舍（David Risher）更换了首席执行官洛根·格林（Logan Green），后者表示该公司需要精简业务并重新关注司机和乘客。格林此前表示，Lyft 需要增加支出才能与 Uber 竞争。</p><h3> Dropbox 裁员</h3><p>云存储公司也无法免受当前金融环境的影响。 4 月份，Dropbox 表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:50;pos:1" href="https://blog.dropbox.com/topics/company/a-message-from-drew">裁员 500 名员工</a>，约占团队人数的 16%。联合创始人德鲁·休斯顿 (Drew Houston) 将此次裁员归咎于经济不景气、业务日趋成熟以及对人工智能日益增长的兴趣的“紧迫性”。休斯顿表示，虽然该公司实现盈利，但其增长正在放缓，一些投资“不再可持续”。</p><h2> 2023 年 3 月</h2><h2></h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-images/2019-06/462235c0-9102-11e9-b76d-3fd26de648d8" data-uuid="1b837daf-2389-37ff-96e8-4345c2dd9e05"><figcaption></figcaption></figure><h3> Roku裁员</h3><p>Roku <a data-i13n="cpos:51;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/roku-layoffs-streaming-2022-201541882.html">于 2022 年底</a>裁员 200 人，但这一计划并未完成。这家流媒体平台创建者于 2023 年 3 月<a data-i13n="cpos:52;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/roku-will-lay-off-another-200-workers-132908304.html">又解雇了 200 名员工</a>。和以前一样，该公司辩称需要抑制不断增长的开支，并专注于那些影响最大的项目。 Roku 一直在艰难应对经济不景气和流媒体视频热潮结束的双重打击。</p><h3> Lucid汽车公司裁员</h3><p>如果您认为豪华电动汽车制造商特别容易受到经济动荡的影响，那么您猜对了。 Lucid Motors 在 3 月份表示，将<a data-i13n="cpos:53;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/lucid-motors-is-laying-off-1300-workers-to-reduce-expenses-090908953.html">裁员 18%</a> ，即约 1,300 人。该品牌仍未达到生产目标，据报道，这些削减有助于应对“不断变化的业务需求和生产力提高”。裁员也是全面的，包括高管和承包商。</p><h3> Meta（Facebook）裁员</h3><p>Meta <a data-i13n="cpos:54;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-mass-layoffs-facebook-111406126.html">在 2022 年秋季</a>裁员 11,000 人，但这还没有结束。 2023年3月，该公司宣布计划<a data-i13n="cpos:55;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/zuckerberg-touts-year-of-efficiency-as-meta-lays-off-an-additional-10000-workers-131957819.html">再裁员1万名</a>，以进一步削减成本。第一次裁员影响了其招聘团队，但该公司<a data-i13n="cpos:56;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-begins-its-latest-round-of-layoffs-145019127.html">在 4 月下旬</a>缩减了技术团队，并<a data-i13n="cpos:57;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-is-laying-off-employees-for-the-third-time-in-less-than-three-months-174112198.html">在 5 月下旬</a>缩减了业务部门。 Facebook 所有者希望通过减少管理层并要求一些领导者承担以前为普通员工保留的工作来简化其运营。 Meta 的员工数量可能需要一段时间才能再次增长——预计要到 2023 年底完成重组工作后才会解除招聘冻结。</p><h2> 2023 年 2 月</h2><h2></h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/0d02d0e0-b856-11ed-bdff-3b6b0c6afd32" data-uuid="1f440042-5788-3939-9ef5-bbd6dc7740b1"><figcaption></figcaption></figure><h3>里维安裁员</h3><p>Rivian <a data-i13n="cpos:58;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/rivian-ceo-memo-cost-cutting-layoffs-205556718.html">在 2022 年</a>进行了裁员，但这不足以帮助这个羽翼未丰的电动汽车品牌实现盈利。 2 月份，该公司又解雇了<a data-i13n="cpos:59;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/rivian-layoffs-184047174.html">6% 的员工</a>，即约 840 名员工。该公司仍在努力实现盈利，而供应链问题造成的产量短缺也无济于事。首席执行官 RJ Scaringe 表示，裁员将帮助 Rivian 专注于其业务“影响最大”的方面。</p><h3>变焦裁员</h3><p>Zoom 是<a data-i13n="cpos:60;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/zoom-earnings-214253721.html">疫情高峰期</a>远程工作文化的主要内容，因此，随着人们返回办公室，该公司削减开支也就不足为奇了。这家视频通话公司 2 月份表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:61;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/zoom-layoffs-202256575.html">裁员约 1,300 名员工</a>，占其员工总数的 15%。正如首席执行官埃里克·袁(Eric Yuan)所说，该公司在应对突如其来的成功时并没有“可持续地”招聘员工。据报道，裁员对于帮助度过困难的经济是必要的。管理团队提供的不仅仅是道歉。袁征将下一财年的工资削减 98%，而所有其他高管的基本工资以及 2023 财年奖金将减少 20%。</p><h3>雅虎裁员</h3><p>Engadget 的母公司雅虎也未能幸免于裁员。该互联网品牌在 2 月份表示，将在 2023 年<a data-i13n="cpos:62;pos:1" href="https://www.axios.com/2023/02/09/yahoo-layoffs-2023-tech-media-companies">裁员超过 20%</a> ，即超过 1,600 人。其中大部分裁员（即大约 1,000 个职位）是立即进行的。不过，首席执行官吉姆·兰佐尼(Jim Lanzone)并未将裁员归咎于经济状况。相反，他将其定位为广告技术部门的重组，因为该部门放弃了一项不盈利的业务，​​转而支持一项成功的业务。实际上，雅虎正在退出与谷歌和 Meta 在广告市场的直接竞争。</p><h3>戴尔裁员</h3><p>大流行病的复苏和严峻的经济形势对个人电脑制造商的打击尤为严重，而戴尔所感受到的痛苦比大多数公司都要严重。在经历了残酷的第四季度（计算机出货量估计下降了 37%）之后，<a data-i13n="cpos:63;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/dell-layoffs-144303513.html">该公司在 2 月初解雇了 5% 的</a>员工，即大约 6,650 名员工。戴尔表示，过去的成本削减努力还不够，据报道需要裁员和精简组织才能重回正轨。</p><h3> Deliveroo裁员</h3><p>送餐服务蓬勃发展，而新冠肺炎 (COVID-19) 疫情让人们远离餐馆，现在人们愿意再次外出就餐，至少有些人感受到了刺痛。 Deliveroo 将<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:64;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://deliveroo.co.uk/more/news-articles/will-shu-message-to-deliveroo-employees" data-original-link="https://deliveroo.co.uk/more/news-articles/will-shu-message-to-deliveroo-employees">解雇约 350 名员工</a>，占其员工总数的 9%。创始人 Will Shu 表示，“重新部署”将使这个数字接近 300 人。理由很熟悉：舒表示，Deliveroo 迅速招聘员工来应对与疫情相关的“前所未有”的增长，但据报道，该公司在应对困难的经济形势时必须削减成本。</p><h3> DocuSign 裁员</h3><p>对于许多在线签署过文件的人来说，DocuSign 可能很熟悉，但这并没有使其免受恶劣经济环境的影响。该公司在 2 月中旬表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:65;pos:1" href="https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1261333/000126133323000007/docu-20230216.htm">裁员 10%</a> 。虽然没有透露具体人数，但截至 2022 年初，该公司拥有 7,461 名员工。大多数失业人员在 DocuSign 的全球现场组织工作。</p><h3>亚搏体育appGitLab裁员</h3><p>您可能不知道 GitLab，但它的 DevOps（开发和运营）平台支撑着 NVIDIA 和 T-Mobile 等科技品牌的工作，而其客户业务的萎缩正在影响其利润。 GitLab 将<a data-i13n="cpos:66;pos:1" href="https://about.gitlab.com/blog/2023/02/09/gitlab-news/">解雇 7% 的员工</a>，即大约 114 人。公司首席执行官西德·西布兰迪 (Sid Sijbrandij) 表示，经济问题意味着客户对软件投资采取“更加保守的方式”，而公司之前重新调整支出的尝试不足以应对这些挑战。</p><h3> GoDaddy 裁员</h3><p>GoDaddy 在疫情爆发初期就进行了裁员，当时其面向零售的社交平台裁掉了 800 多名员工。然而，今年二月，它采取了更广泛的行动。该网络服务提供商解雇了所有部门<a data-i13n="cpos:67;pos:1" href="https://aboutus.godaddy.net/newsroom/press-releases/press-release-details/2023/A-message-from-GoDaddy-CEO-Aman-Bhutani/default.aspx">8% 的员工</a>，即 500 多人。首席执行官阿曼·布塔尼 (Aman Bhutani) 声称，其他形式的成本削减不足以帮助公司应对“不确定”的经济形势，这反映了进一步整合 Main Street Hub 等收购的努力。</p><h3> Twilio 裁员</h3><p>Twilio 在 2022 年 9 月裁减了 800 多个工作岗位，但随着 2023 年开始，它进行了更大幅度的裁员。该云通信品牌在 2 月中旬<a data-i13n="cpos:68;pos:1" href="https://www.twilio.com/blog/restructuring-twilio">解雇了 17% 的员工</a>，即大约 1,500 人。与许多其他科技公司一样，Twillio 表示，过去的成本削减努力不足以承受严酷的环境。它还将裁员合理化，以精简组织。</p><h2> 2023 年 1 月</h2><h2></h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-05/f50d6cc0-d84a-11ec-b3ed-100a619b2c97" alt="2022 年 5 月 16 日，在参观位于美国加利福尼亚州山景城的谷歌新湾景园区时，BV100 大楼的外景。照片摄于 2022 年 5 月 16 日。REUTERS/Peter DaSilva" data-uuid="018fa580-4a3a-3a88-9d3f-09be5f04dff4"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">路透社/彼得·达席尔瓦</div></figure><h3>谷歌（Alphabet）裁员</h3><p>谷歌母公司 Alphabet 一段时间以来一直在削减成本，包括<a data-i13n="cpos:69;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-shutting-down-stadia-162704135.html">关闭 Stadia</a> ，但该公司在 1 月底更进一步，表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:70;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-parent-alphabet-is-laying-off-12000-employees-105523115.html">裁员 12,000 名员工</a>。首席执行官桑达尔·皮查伊 (Sundar Pichai) 毫不掩饰其理由：Alphabet 一直在针对“不同的经济现实”进行招聘，并正在进行重组，以专注于这家互联网巨头最重要的业务。这一决定对该公司 120 区孵化器的打击<a data-i13n="cpos:71;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-lays-off-most-employees-area-120-in-house-incubator-154329887.html">尤为严重</a>，该部门的大多数员工都失业了。 Intrinsic（机器人）和 Verily（健康）等子品牌也在大规模裁员前几天裁掉了大量员工。 Waymo 已<a data-i13n="cpos:72;pos:1" href="https://www.reuters.com/article/alphabet-layoffs-waymo-idCAKBN2V33PW">进行</a>两轮裁员，裁员 209 人，占员工总数的 8%。</p><h3>亚马逊裁员</h3><p>亚马逊去年秋天就已经 <a data-i13n="cpos:73;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-layoffs-report-191003720.html">制定了裁员计划</a>，但在 1 月初扩大了裁员范围，表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:74;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-expanded-job-cuts-18000-102059372.html">裁减 18,000 个工作岗位</a>，其中大部分来自零售和招聘团队。 3 月份，该公司<a data-i13n="cpos:75;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-will-lay-off-another-9000-employees-in-the-coming-weeks-152653190.html">又裁员 9,000 人</a>，4 月份又表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:76;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-lays-off-more-than-100-employees-across-its-gaming-divisions-190634108.html">有 100 多名游戏员工</a>离职。毫不奇怪，首席执行官安迪·贾西（Andy Jassy）将其归咎于“经济的不确定性”和近年来的快速招聘。随着人们转向网上购物，亚马逊从这一流行病中<a data-i13n="cpos:77;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-q1-2021-210221698.html">受益匪浅</a>，但随着人们回归实体店，其<a data-i13n="cpos:78;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/amazon-q1-2022-earnings-growth-235926922.html">增长正在放缓</a>。</p><h3> Coinbase 裁员</h3><p>Coinbase 是受 2022 年加密货币市场低迷影响的较大公司之一，这种影响一直延续到新的一年。该加密货币交易所在 1 月中旬<a data-i13n="cpos:79;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/coinbase-lay-offs-reduced-expenses-153433234.html">裁员 950 人</a>，而就在几个月前，该<a data-i13n="cpos:80;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/coinbase-job-cuts-layoffs-150838290.html">交易所还裁员 1,100 人</a>。这是大型科技品牌中比例最大的裁员之一——Coinbase 裁掉了约五分之一的员工。首席执行官布莱恩·阿姆斯特朗表示，他的公司需要裁员来缩减运营开支，并度过他之前所说的“加密货币冬天”，但这也意味着取消一些不太可能成功的项目。</p><h3> IBM裁员</h3><p>裁员有时更多地源于公司战略转变，而不是财务困难，IBM 在 2023 年提供了一个典型的例子。这家计算先驱在剥离了人工智能驱动的 Watson Health 业务和基础设施管理部门（现为 Kyndryl）后，于 1 月下旬<a data-i13n="cpos:81;pos:1" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-01-25/ibm-to-cut-about-3-900-workers-still-hiring-in-higher-growth-areas?sref=10lNAhZ9">裁减了 3,900 个工作岗位。</a> ）在秋天。简而言之，随着 IBM 转向云计算，这些员工没有什么可做的。</p><h3>微软裁员</h3><p>微软开始了公司历史上第二大裁员潮，该公司表示将在 1 月中旬至 3 月底期间<a data-i13n="cpos:82;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-confirms-layoffs-151816595.html">裁员 10,000 人</a>。与许多其他科技巨头一样，随着客户在大流行复苏期间<a data-i13n="cpos:83;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-q2-fy23-earnings-report-211718819.html">缩减支出</a>（特别是在 Windows 和设备上），该公司正在削减成本。这种裁员对一些部门来说尤其痛苦——据报道，他们<a data-i13n="cpos:84;pos:1" href="https://www.windowscentral.com/microsoft/microsoft-has-laid-off-entire-teams-behind-virtual-mixed-reality-and-hololens">摧毁了 HoloLens 和混合现实团队</a>，而 343 Industries 则在失去数十名员工后据信正在<a data-i13n="cpos:85;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/343-industries-halo-unreal-engine-202439779.html">重启 Halo 开发</a>。 GitHub 正在<a data-i13n="cpos:86;pos:1" href="https://siliconangle.com/2023/02/09/github-gitlab-announce-job-cuts/">裁员 10%</a> ，即大约 300 人。</p><h3>贝宝裁员</h3><p>PayPal 一直是健康状况较好的大型科技公司之一，去年第三季度的<a data-i13n="cpos:87;pos:1" href="https://s201.q4cdn.com/231198771/files/doc_financials/2022/q3/PYPL-Q3-22-Earnings-Release.pdf">业绩超出了预期</a>。尽管如此，它也未能幸免于经济不景气的影响。这家在线支付公司于 1 月底公布了<a data-i13n="cpos:88;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/paypal-is-laying-off-2000-employees-212108119.html">裁员 2,000 名员工</a>的计划，占其员工总数的 7%。首席执行官丹·舒尔曼 (Dan Schulman) 声称，裁员将控制成本，并帮助 PayPal 专注于“核心战略重点”。</p><h3> Salesforce 裁员</h3><p>Salesforce 为 2023 年定下了基调，在新年仅四天后，该公司就警告称将<a data-i13n="cpos:89;pos:1" href="https://www.sec.gov/ix?doc=/Archives/edgar/data/0001108524/000110852423000003/crm-20230104.htm">裁员 8,000 名员工</a>，约占员工总数的 10%。尽管该云软件品牌在疫情期间蓬勃发展，收入快速增长，但它承认在繁荣时期过于积极地招聘员工，在经济衰退时无法维持这一员工水平。</p><h3> SAP裁员</h3><p>商业软件巨头 SAP 的利润在 2022 年底大幅下降 68%，并从 2023 年开始<a data-i13n="cpos:90;pos:1" href="https://news.sap.com/2023/01/sap-announces-fourth-quarter-and-full-year-2022-results/">裁员 2,800 名员工</a>以保持业务健康发展。不过，与科技领域的一些知名企业不同的是，SAP 并没有将裁员归咎于大流行时期的过度招聘。相反，它将这一举措描述为一家仍预计 2023 年加速增长的公司的“有针对性的重组”。</p><h3> Spotify 裁员</h3><p>近年来，Spotify 大力投资<a data-i13n="cpos:91;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2020-02-05-spotify-podcasts-the-ringer.html">扩大其播客帝国</a>，但在 2023 年开始时很快就停止了这种做法。这家流媒体音乐服务公司在 1 月底表示，将<a data-i13n="cpos:92;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-will-lay-off-6-percent-of-employees-130337498.html">裁员 6%</a> （截至第三季度，Spotify 有 9,800 名员工），同时进行重组工作，其中包括内容主管 Dawn Ostroff 的离职。尽管 2022 年的高级订阅用户数量比以往任何时候都多，但该公司也<a data-i13n="cpos:93;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-reaches-205-million-premium-subscribers-as-losses-mount-122503157.html">遭受了巨大损失</a>——首席执行官丹尼尔·埃克 (Daniel Ek) 表示，在收入无法支撑之前，他的投资“过于雄心勃勃”。</p><h3> Wayfair裁员</h3><p>亚马逊并不是唯一一家在 2023 年缩减规模的大型在线零售商。Wayfair 在 1 月底表示，将<a data-i13n="cpos:94;pos:1" href="https://investor.wayfair.com/news/news-details/2023/Wayfair-Announces-Update-to-Cost-Efficiency-Plan-and-Business-Performance/default.aspx">裁员 1,750 名团队成员</a>，占其全球员工总数的 10%。其中约 1,200 名员工被裁减，目的是“消除管理层”，并以其他方式帮助公司变得更精简、更灵活。 Wayfair 自 2022 年 8 月以来一直在削减成本（包括 870 个职位），但认为裁员有助于其比预期更早实现盈亏平衡。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/big-tech-layoffs-2023-152856197.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/big-tech-layoffs-2023-152856197.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> ebb49371-5396-4cbe-9ddd-56da42a4f377 </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jon Fingas,Engadget Team]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Mon, 16 Oct 2023 15:52:41 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1706117363</ingested><modified> 2024-01-24T17:29:44+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Unemployment Issues]]></category><category><![CDATA[Budget, Tax & Economy]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="888" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-01%2F94cbe9d0-9cc7-11ed-9daf-521efd1c29f0&amp;resize=1400%2C888&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=db76f83910f1c0b57e7081a2536ac42a4de08016" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="888" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-01%2F94cbe9d0-9cc7-11ed-9daf-521efd1c29f0&amp;resize=1400%2C888&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=e862820c339c78e373368fe41d3892936169b304" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Westend61 via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Businessman carrying box with personal belongings on sunny day]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Esports are messy in 2024 | This week's gaming news]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>在《守望先锋联赛》 <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-overwatch-league-appears-to-be-over-210054506.html">消亡仅几个月后</a>，就有消息称暴雪和 ESL FACEIT 正准备为<em>《守望先锋 2》</em>推出<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/blizzard-partners-with-esl-for-an-open-overwatch-2-esports-circuit-170033793.html">新的电子竞技巡回赛</a>，现在正是盘点整个电子竞技界的好时机。事情看起来有点疯狂，至少在北美是这样。 <em>《英雄联盟》</em>和<em>《火箭联盟》</em>的情况尤其混乱，进入 2024 年赛季时预算紧缩，而且发生了重大调整。同时，公开预选赛模式的扩展将为普通玩家提供更多机会参加<em>《Valorant》</em> 、 <em>《守望先锋 2》</em> 、 <em>《火箭联盟》</em>和各种格斗游戏。伙计们，准备好手指吧。 </p><div id="6da602ea2e1f4a9c9574e66f8f5a1c00"><div style="left:0;width:100%;height:0;position:relative;padding-bottom:56.25%;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/j4dSu-PsVv0?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no" data-embed-domain="www.youtube.com"></iframe></div></div><h2>本周的故事</h2><h3>2024 年 Xbox 产品阵容</h3><p>Xbox 上周举行了 2024 年首次展示会，重点展示了一些已经开发多年的游戏。 <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/indiana-jones-and-the-great-circle-is-coming-to-xbox-and-pc-later-this-year-212759483.html"><em>《夺宝奇兵：大圆环》</em></a>将于 2024 年晚些时候推出，由<em>《德军总部 II：新巨像》</em>工作室 MachineGames 制作。新的镜头展示了很多鞭打、讽刺和纳粹拳打脚踢的场面，就像印第想要的那样。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>接下来，Obsidian 的大型奇幻角色扮演游戏<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/avowed-obsidians-big-fantasy-rpg-will-land-in-fall-2024-203343619.html"><em>Avowed</em></a>将于秋季登陆 PC 和 Xbox。 Obsidian 是<em>《辐射：新维加斯》</em>和<em>《天外世界》</em>的工作室，而<em>《Avowed》</em>看起来就像是《上古卷轴》游戏的​​翻版。</p><p>最后， <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/senuas-saga-hellblade-ii-finally-arrives-on-may-21-203751802.html"><em>《塞娜的传奇：地狱之刃 II》</em></a>将于 5 月 21 日推出，距离它与 Xbox Series X 一起发布已经过去了将近五年。</p><h3>电子竞技卷土重来，规模比以往任何时候都小</h3><p>2024 年是电子竞技的清算时刻，尤其是在北美。暴雪去年砍掉了《守望先锋联赛》，并试图与ESL开始新的系列赛，北美<em>英雄联盟</em>的收视率正在下降，<em>火箭联盟</em>的RLCS锦标赛也处于剧变状态。</p><p><em>英雄联盟</em>是电子竞技之王，2023 年，在韩国和中国队伍的传奇表现的推动下，其世界锦标赛打破了收视率记录——好吧，主要是 Faker。但无论我多么努力地为他们加油，北美<em>英雄联盟</em>队伍在世界舞台上仍然是一个笑话。去年，韩国夏季赛吸引了 150 万同时观看者，而 LCS 夏季赛的观看人数峰值为 22.3 万人，低于 2022 年的 37 万。2024 赛季本月以地区锦标赛拉开帷幕，北美 LCS 看起来像是一种全新的野兽。 LCS 的参赛队伍数量从 10 支减少到 8 支，这意味着邪恶天才队和黄金卫士队都消失了，联盟在常规赛中采用更快节奏的单局两胜赛制。我们将在 5 月份的 MSI 上看到这一切如何得到回报。</p><p>在火箭联盟冠军系列赛中，预算紧张且队伍分散。今年将有两场大型比赛，而不是三场，再加上世界锦标赛，北美和欧洲的名额较少。六名知名解说员退出了今年的赛事，看起来只有北美和欧洲会举办比赛，而且只有英语。今年 RLCS 的奖金池也有所减少，从 600 万美元降至 430 万美元。进入 2024 年，少数球队失去了赞助，现有组织中也出现了大量的球员变动。最重要的是，该游戏最著名的玩家 Squishy 宣布计划退出职业比赛，专注于流媒体。这只是<em>火箭联盟</em>电子竞技中一个令人困惑的时期。</p><p>电子竞技缩减的一个副作用是向公开预选赛的转变。<em>火箭联盟</em>今年改为公开预选赛，这意味着基本上任何人都可以争夺 RLCS 的席位，而不是球队购买赛季门票。 RLCS 的奖金池虽然较小，但更深，并且北美排名前 128 的球队将获得少量奖金。</p><p>自 2020 年游戏推出以来， <em>《Valorant》</em>电子竞技场景一直在稳步发展，2023 年《Valorant》冠军巡回赛的观众人数达到峰值 140 万。 VCT 一直以公开预选赛为特色，今年该系统随着 Premier 的推出而扩展，Premier 是游戏内的竞技赛道，可作为日常玩家在主舞台上竞争的另一个渠道。 （作为附带说明， <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J8TKKbMcBic">VCT游戏改变者</a>系列突出显示了边缘化性别的玩家，这真的很棒，请在某个时候检查一下。）</p><p>就在本周，暴雪宣布了《守望先锋冠军》系列，这是<em>守望先锋2</em>的多区域电子竞技锦标赛。与已故的《守望先锋联赛》不同，冠军系列将有开放的预选赛。新系列是由沙特阿拉伯的公共投资基金所有的ESL Faceit制作的，这让我很难过。</p><p>同时，格斗游戏社区已经进行了一段时间的公开注册。 EVO是当年最大的格斗比赛比赛，在2023年，它接待了9,000多名冠军比赛。作为一对一的类型，格斗游戏经常发现自己在电子竞技的实验前线上，而evo始终是个好时机。</p><p>我认为，开放式注册是电子竞技的一个很酷的举动 - 它允许更多来自不同背景的人参与，并为年轻专业人士提供了可持续的入口点。这就是人才管道的建造方式。</p><h3>正在播放</h3><div id="c7b820c3e2ed4985b9868566a070b09b"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/X0ttwM9-1YA?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no" data-embed-domain="www.youtube.com"></iframe></div><p>在花了几个月的时间玩其他游戏后，我又回到了<em>羊羔的崇拜</em>。肉体更新的自由罪上周降落了，它很大又性感，在游戏中增加了放荡的层次和许多新内容。正如Engadget周末编辑Cheyenne MacDonald <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sins-of-the-flesh-adds-longevity-and-sex-to-cult-of-the-lamb-130041583.html">在她的评论中说的</a>那样：“我们的追随者和追随者都度过了愉快的时光。”</p>本文最初出现在https://www.engadget.com/esports-are-messy-in-2024-this-weeks-gaming-news-news-news-news-news-news-news-news-news-news-news-news-170043963.html?src=rsss]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/esports-are-messy-in-2024-this-weeks-gaming-news-170043963.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> E8D56EE2-C37B-46DA-955D-456E9CB1B81E </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jessica Conditt]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 24 Jan 2024 17:00:43 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1706114999</ingested><modified> 2024-01-24T16：50：13+00：00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Sports & Recreation]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jessica Conditt]]></category><media:content height="787" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2Ff0d9bef0-bad0-11ee-a5de-53ee63e84933&amp;resize=1400%2C787&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=86696f06243338b65f5e037f62f9e9812ad02236" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="787" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2Ff0d9bef0-bad0-11ee-a5de-53ee63e84933&amp;resize=1400%2C787&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=a171b7510295a67c91450411594e142eac48d726" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA["Esports in 2024" for Engadget's weekly video game news show. Overwatch 2, League of Legends and Rocket League are displayed.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Esports in 2024]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The 6 best budgeting apps to replace Mint in 2024]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>如果您还没有听说过，流行的预算应用程序 Mint <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/intuit-is-closing-down-mint-its-popular-free-budget-tracking-app-054145229.html">即将消失</a>。母公司 Intuit 将于 2024 年 3 月 24 日关闭该服务。该公司建议人们迁移到其另一款个人理财应用程序<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Credit Karma;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=5bdc3e3e-e02c-4b63-90d8-efcfab9d703c&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Credit+Karma&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5jcmVkaXRrYXJtYS5jb20vIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJkZDEyODJjMy05OWVkLTRkZGMtYjhhYi1jMTBjNjBkNGU3MGMifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAVpjPP_H09LvIBKR1-ty59U8Y-n767pvLq6sBaflXg4C&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.creditkarma.com%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.creditkarma.com/">Credit Karma</a> 。 <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-11-01/intuit-winds-down-personal-finance-app-mint-shifts-users-to-credit-karma?sref=10lNAhZ9#xj4y7vzkg">据<em>彭博社</em>报道</a>，截至 2021 年，Mint 拥有 360 万活跃用户，我就是其中之一。我使用该应用程序在一个地方跟踪我的所有帐户，而无需登录太多不同的银行应用程序。但我也用它来监控我的信用评分，坚持每月预算，并设定目标，例如建立应急基金或更快地偿还抵押贷款。因此，寻找 Credit Karma 之外的 Mint 替代方案成为当务之急。</p><p> Intuit 尚未评论是否打算将 Mint 的预算功能纳入 Credit Karma，但就目前情况而言，Credit Karma 并不是 Mint 的替代品：它的目的是监控您的信用，并且 Intuit 希望引导您使用信用卡和各种其他金融产品。我下载了它，花了一些时间使用它，但没有留下深刻的印象。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>因此，此外，我最近安装了六个竞争性的货币应用程序，看看是否有任何可以将其作为永久的 Mint 替代品。以下是我想阅读的指南：对承诺在一个地方跟踪您的净资产和支出的预算应用程序进行比较。我还承诺更新本指南，因为我测试的各种应用程序将继续添加更多功能，并在某些情况下纠正已知的错误。当我掉进兔子洞时加入我。</p><h2>我们如何测试</h2><p>首先，我必须做一些研究。为了找到要测试的应用程序列表，我咨询了值得信赖的谷歌（甚至更值得信赖的 Reddit）；阅读 App Store 上流行应用程序的评论；还询问朋友和同事他们可能正在使用哪些预算跟踪应用程序。我发现的一些应用程序是免费的，就像 Mint 一样。当然，这些会显示大量广告（对不起，“优惠”）以维持业务。但大多数可用的应用程序都需要付费订阅，价格通常最高约为每年 100 美元，或每月 15 美元。 （剧透：我的首选比那便宜。）</p><p>由于本指南旨在帮助 Mint 用户找到永久替代品，因此我选择测试的任何服务都需要完成几件事：将所有帐户数据导入到一个位置；提供预算工具；并跟踪您的支出、净资产和信用评分。除非另有说明，所有这些应用程序均可在 iOS、Android 和网络上使用。</p><p>一旦我有了六个应用程序的候选名单，我就开始设置它们。为了彻底测试这些应用程序（请记住，我自己确实在寻找<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-best-budgeting-apps-to-replace-mint-143047346.html">Mint 替代品</a>），我特意将每个帐户添加到每个跟踪应用程序中，无论余额有多么小或无关紧要。接下来是名副其实的双因素身份验证<em>土拨鼠日</em>。只需几个小时即可输入密码和一次性密码，为同一家银行输入六次以上。希望您只需执行此操作一次。</p><h2>如何从 Mint 导入财务数据</h2><p>如果从 Mint 导入数据就像从新的预算应用程序中输入您的凭据并点击“导入”一样简单就好了。事实上，任何宣传能够从 Mint 移植统计数据的应用程序都只会让你上传包含交易和其他数据的 CSV 文件。</p><p>要从 Mint 下载 CSV 文件，请执行以下操作：</p><ol><li><p>登录 Mint.com 并点击屏幕左侧菜单中的<strong>“交易”</strong> 。</p></li><li><p>选择一个帐户或<strong>所有帐户</strong>。</p></li><li><p>向下滚动并查找较小字体的“<strong>导出[数量]交易</strong>”。</p></li><li><p>您的 CSV 文件应该开始下载。</p></li></ol><p>注意：按帐户下载可能看起来更烦人，但如果您使用的应用程序允许您将交易一对一导入到相应的帐户中，则可以帮助您在另一端进行设置。</p><h2>最好的 Mint 替代品：Quicken Simplifi </h2><p><core-commerce id="bb20dc45b8324009aa9cd29e1a2a1e55" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p></p><p>无意双关，但我喜欢<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Quicken;elmt:;cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=36291888-36d6-4b83-80bb-f82004bcfdb1&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Quicken&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5xdWlja2VuLmNvbS9wcm9kdWN0cy9zaW1wbGlmaS8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImRkMTI4MmMzLTk5ZWQtNGRkYy1iOGFiLWMxMGM2MGQ0ZTcwYyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAYeMh4c5W9UJ4jn4z86v7Pa70haIXDE9DNo8JoufbXCN&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.quicken.com%2Fproducts%2Fsimplifi%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.quicken.com/products/simplifi/">Quicken Simplifi</a>的原因是它的简单性。虽然其他应用程序试图通过深色主题和可自定义表情符号来区分自己，但 Simplifi 拥有干净的用户界面，您只需不断滚动即可获得所有统计数据的详细概述。其中包括您的顶线余额；净值;最近的支出；即将到来的定期付款；您的支出计划的快照；支出最高的类别；成就；以及您设置的任何监视列表。您还可以在应用程序的其他位置设置储蓄目标。我也很欣赏它如何提供整洁、几乎有趣的可视化效果，而又不会显得杂乱。大约一天后，我在移动和网络仪表板中感到宾至如归，这比我适应一些竞争服务要快（我正在看着你们，YNAB 和 Monarch）。</p><p>使用 Simplifi 进行设置基本上是轻松的。给我留下特别深刻印象的是它与富达的联系是多么容易；无论出于何种原因，并非所有预算跟踪器都这样做。这也是我测试过的唯一一项可以让您选择邀请配偶或财务顾问共同管理您的账户的服务之一。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/9003a9c0-9dd8-11ee-8bf5-613f22f37439" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/9003a9c0-9dd8-11ee-8bf5-613f22f37439" style="height:1482px;width:1512px;" alt="的屏幕截图" data-uuid="ab274afb-4089-34d7-8710-7a5bffec9201"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">达纳沃尔曼/Engadget</div></figure><p>实际上，Simplifi 对我的一些开支进行了错误分类，但与这些预算追踪器相比并没有什么异常。当您查看交易时，您还可以标记是否期望退款，这是我测试的服务中的一个独特功能。 Simplifi 还比我测试过的其他一些应用程序更好地估算了我的常规收入。最重要的是，我很高兴能够将一些（但不是全部）从商家购买的商品归类为重复购买。例如，我可以将我的两次亚马逊订阅并保存添加为定期付款，而不必为每次亚马逊购买创建广泛的规则。</p><p>预算功能也是不言自明的。只需检查您的常规收入是否准确，并确保设置定期付款，记下哪些是账单，哪些是订阅。这很重要，因为 Simplifi 会向您显示您的实得总收入以及“账单后收入”数字。这个数字包括账单，但不包括任意订阅。从那里，您可以在“计划支出”桶中按类别添加支出目标。计划支出还可以包括一次性支出，而不仅仅是每月预算。当您创建预算时，Simplifi 会根据六个月的平均值建议一个数字。</p><p>这不是破坏交易的因素，但在开始使用时要记住两件事：Simplifi 值得注意的是，您无法通过 Apple 或 Google 设置帐户。尽管 Quicken 承诺“30 天退款保证”，但也没有免费试用的选择。</p><h2>最佳 Mint 替代品（亚军）：Monarch Money </h2><p><core-commerce id="9f80c5fd1fd4460fae9fdf2cf5fbbe33" data-type="product-list" data-original-url="https://www.monarchmoney.com/"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5tb25hcmNobW9uZXkuY29tLyIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiZGQxMjgyYzMtOTllZC00ZGRjLWI4YWItYzEwYzYwZDRlNzBjIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAcWs5pONCUeC031DwLIWoLY9cIulXQ--M-1DkcI1Uv2T&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.monarchmoney.com%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.monarchmoney.com/">君主金钱</a>在我身上增长。我对该应用程序的第一个印象是由前薄荷产品经理创立的，它比该列表中的其他应用程序更难使用，包括Simplifi，Nerdwallet和Copilot。确实如此。例如，编辑费用类别，添加经常性交易并创建规则，比其需要的要复杂得多，尤其是在移动应用中。 （我的建议：使用Web应用程序进行微调细节。）Monarch也没有正确的收入；我不得不编辑它。</p><p>不过，一旦您设置了一旦，Monarch就会提供令人印象深刻的粒度水平。在“预算”部分中，您可以看到一个真正的资产负债表，显示每个类别的预算和实际情况。您还会找到一年或按月的预测。而且经常性支出不仅可以由商人设置，还可以设置其他参数。例如，虽然大多数亚马逊购买可能被标记为“购物”，但这些价格为54.18美元或34.18美元，肯定是婴儿用品，并且每次都可以自动将其标记为这样，更不用说被编程为经常性付款了。但是，奇怪的是，没有办法将某些经常性付款标记为账单。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/87df1700-9dda-11ee-bbff-f06ef106aa46" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/87df1700-9dda-11ee-bbff-f06ef106aa46" style="height:1482px;width:1512px;" alt="的屏幕截图" data-uuid="e01b1f91-522e-3af0-90fa-b79dd5951a6e"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">达纳沃尔曼/Engadget</div></figure><p>在我在2023年12月首次发布此故事后不久，Monarch <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5tb25hcmNobW9uZXkuY29tL3doYXRzLW5ldy9yZXBvcnRzLWNhbmFkYS1pbXByb3ZlZC1zeW5jaW5nIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJkZDEyODJjMy05OWVkLTRkZGMtYjhhYi1jMTBjNjBkNGU3MGMifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAfLytYpt0ASBsMQ4WC_G2DiCwVk_VpeUTW3alC1f6wgZ&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.monarchmoney.com%2Fwhats-new%2Freports-canada-improved-syncing" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.monarchmoney.com/whats-new/reports-canada-improved-syncing">引入了</a>一个详细的报告部分，您可以根据帐户，类别和标签之类的内容创建按需图表。该功能暂时仅在该应用程序的Web版本上可用。作为同一更新的一部分，Monarch增加了对聚合器的支持，这使得可以自动更新汽车的价值。这些功能也很可能吸引了那些更喜欢动手管理财务状况的电力用户。</p><p>移动应用程序主要是不言自明的。主仪表板显示您的净资产；您最近的四项交易；一个月的支出比较；收入月的收入；即将到来的账单；投资快照；您设定的任何目标的列表；最后，您的评论一个月链接。评估一个月比大多数人更详细，研究了现金流。最高收入和费用类别；现金流趋势；更改您的净资产，资产和负债；加上资产和责任分解。</p><p>在主屏幕上，您还可以找到帐户，交易，现金流，预算和经常性的选项卡。像这里有许多其他应用程序一样，Monarch可以自动实现重复的费用和收入，即使该类别错误。 （他们都在一定程度上做。）费用类别以表情符号为标志，如果您愿意，您可以自定义。</p><p> Monarch Money使用网络的组合与银行建立联系，包括MasterCard拥有的竞争网络，包括格子， <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.mx.com/">MX</a>和精致。 （在本指南结束时，我有一个快速解释器（该领域的行业标准）。）作为12月下旬更新的一部分，君主还使通过其他两个网络连接变得更加容易理性格子失败。与Nerdwallet类似，我发现自己每次都想越过格子屏幕以添加另一个帐户时都完成了两因素身份验证。值得注意的是，Monarch是我测试过的唯一一个允许您允许您家庭中其他人的应用程序（可能是配偶或财务顾问）。 Monarch还<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://help.simplifimoney.com/en/articles/8545901-how-to-import-transactions-from-mint">具有从MINT导入的Chrome扩展名</a>，尽管实际上这只是下载CSV文件的快捷方式，无论您选择在哪里获取MINT数据，都必须执行此操作。</p><p>即将推出，君主表示，它正在增加投资交易的同步。法案跟踪；实现目标设定的更详细和“直观”的方法；和移动设备上的净值图。君主还没有为大多数项目提供时间表，只是说改进的目标功能将于2024年初出现。</p><h2>最好的新手：副作用金钱</h2><p><core-commerce id="cb581f0fec1b41feafe2ea7de4181289" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://copilot.money/">Copilot Money</a>可能是我测试过的最好的预算跟踪器。至少目前，它也具有iOS和MAC独有的区别。该公司首席执行官Andres Ugarte已公开承诺，Android和Web应用程序将于2024年推出（Ugarte告诉我，更可能是下半年）。但是，在跟随它之前，我不能为大多数拥有这么多竞争者的人推荐Copilot。 </p><div id="d08e9e7205454c8597072884a431740e"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">Copilot用于网络和Android！<br><br>多亏了我们用户的支持，以及我们从薄荷迁移的人们看到的压倒性积极接待，我们现在可以说我们将构建<a href="https://twitter.com/copilotmoney?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@copilotmoney</a> for Web和Android，目标是在2024年推出。<br><br>我们将继续…</p> - <a href="https://twitter.com/chuga/status/1724839927869755509?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023年11月15日，</a>安德烈斯·乌加特（@chuga）</blockquote></div><p>我会遇到其他功能，我会进入。但这是很有希望的，一个人关注。这只是一个快速，高效，设计良好的应用程序，当他们最终能够下载时，Android用户将可以使用。它可以很好地利用颜色，表情符号和图形，以帮助您了解从预算到投资绩效再到信用卡债务的所有事情，随着时间的流逝。尤其是，Copilot的工作要比几乎任何其他可视化您的经常性每月费用的应用程序要好。</p><p>但是，在这些有力的色彩和可爱的表情符号后面是一些复杂的表演。当您对支出进行分类时，Copilot的AI驱动的“智能”变得更加聪明。 （您还可以添加自己的类别，并选择表情符号。）这并不完美。 Copilot将一些购买（它们都这样做）误导了，但它比大多数人更容易编辑。最重要的是，内部搜索功能非常快。一旦您开始键入，它就会开始降低交易历史记录。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/a1142f30-9dda-11ee-bfbf-0faa85876b37" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/a1142f30-9dda-11ee-bfbf-0faa85876b37" style="height:1482px;width:1512px;" alt="Copilot Money 的 iOS 应用程序的屏幕截图。" data-uuid="0cf492f7-3fda-39b7-ab09-01fa330659c1"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">达纳沃尔曼/Engadget</div></figure><p> Copilot在提供亚马逊和Venmo集成方面也是独一无二的，使您可以查看交易详细信息。使用Amazon，这需要通过应用程序内浏览器登录您的Amazon帐户。对于Venmo，您必须将fwd@copilot.money设置为转发地址，然后创建一个过滤器，其中来自<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="mailto:venmo@venmo.com">venmo@venmo.com</a>的电子邮件自动转发至fwd@copilot.money。</p><p>当该应用程序大量自动化时，我仍然感谢Copilot标志着新的审核交易。这是淘汰欺诈性指控的好方法，并且对您的支出习惯有意义。</p><p>像Monarch Money一样，Copilot最近更新了其应用程序，以使通过格子以外的其他网络更容易连接到银行。作为同一更新的一部分，Copilot表示，它已经改善了与American Express和Fidelity的联系，这再次可能是某些预算跟踪应用程序的错误。</p><p>由于该应用程序相对较新（它于2020年初推出），因此该公司仍在赶上一些餐桌功能的竞争。 Ugarte告诉我，他的团队几乎已经完成了一个详细的现金流部分，该<a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://intelligence.copilot.money/">部分</a>可能在2023年底之前推出，但更有可能在2024年初。它当前的“智能”平台，该平台为其智能支出分类提供动力。其中包括“智能财务目标”，自然语言搜索，聊天界面，预测和基准测试。 Ugarte告诉我，该基准测试的目的是让人们了解与其他副驾驶用户相比的支出和投资绩效。这些功能中的大多数应该在新的一年到达。</p><p> Copilot为新客户做了一些有趣的事情，使它与竞争对手区分开。有一个“演示模式”，感觉就像是游戏模拟器。无需添加自己的帐户。该公司还提供了Ripmint的两个免费月份，这是比大多数人更慷慨的介绍性报价。当它最终到来时，每月7.92美元的计划比某些竞争应用程序便宜，尽管每年95美元的选项处于同一球场。</p><h2>最好的免费预算应用程序：Nerdwallet </h2><p><core-commerce id="39236874c65c492bb3682eddbfa1c0a2" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p></p><p>您可能知道<a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.nerdwallet.com/">Nerdwallet</a>是一个提供个人理财新闻，解释者和指南的网站。当我搜索财务期限时，我经常会看到它，而且可以肯定的是，这是我最有可能单击的网站之一。碰巧的是，Nerdwallet还具有提供我测试的唯一免费预算跟踪应用程序之一的区别。实际上，没有付费版本；没有什么可以锁定在付费墙后面。主要收获：到处都有广告。公平地说，薄荷的免费版本也是如此。</p><p>即使有不可避免的信用卡优惠，Nerdwallet也具有干净，易于理解的用户界面，其中包括Web和移动应用程序。它最突出的关键指标是您的现金流，净资产和信用评分。 （值得注意的是，尽管薄荷本身提供了信用评分监控，但大多数竞争对手都没有。）我特别喜欢每周的见解，这些见解深入探讨了您花费最多的钱或您支付了多少费用，以及如何比较。到上个月。因为这是Nerdwallet，这是财务信息的百科全书，因此在设置帐户时会获得一些特别具体的类别选项（想想：Roth或非Roth IRA）。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/bc32eef0-9dda-11ee-bfa3-00e92921a6eb" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/bc32eef0-9dda-11ee-bfa3-00e92921a6eb" style="height:1482px;width:1512px;" alt="的屏幕截图" data-uuid="5d4cd4ed-f2ab-3c97-addc-64cd0732dcc7"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">达纳沃尔曼/Engadget</div></figure><p>作为一个预算应用程序，如果有点基础，Nerdwallet是可以维修的。像我测试的其他应用程序一样，您可以设置经常出现的账单。重要的是，它遵循流行的50/30/20预算规则，这使您将预算的50％投入了所需的东西，30％的预算规则，剩下的20％以及剩余的20％用于储蓄或债务偿还。如果这对您有用，太好了 - 只知道您不能以与某些竞争应用程序相同的程度自定义预算。您当前无法创建自定义的支出类别，尽管该应用程序仪表板部分中的注释说：“将来您可以自定义它们。”您还不能将项目从想要的列移至“需求”，反之亦然，但是“将来，您将能够移动特定的交易，以积极管理每个组的内容。”不过，书呆子发言人拒绝提供ETA。</p><p>最后，值得注意的是，Nerdwallet是我测试过的任何应用程序中最繁重的设置过程之一。我认为这不是一个破坏者，因为您只需要一次做一次，希望您不会像我那样建立六个或七个应用程序。使Nerdwallet的入职特别乏味的原因是，每次我想添加一个帐户时，我都必须经过两个因子身份验证过程，甚至可以越过格子飞溅屏幕，这并不包括我在每个上设置的2FA我的银行。格子发言人说，这是关于内尔德瓦莱特（Nerdwallet）的末端的安全政策，而不是格子。</p><p>正是因为Nerdwallet是提供信用评分监控的唯一预算跟踪器之一，因此在设置期间，它还需要更多您的个人信息，包括您的生日，地址，电话号码和社会保险号的最后四位数。信用业力也是如此，这也可以进行信用评分监控。</p><p>与设置过程相关的是，我发现Nerdwallet在自动检测我的常规收入时的熟练程度少于其他应用程序。就我而言，它将一次性的一次性电汇视为收入，这时我唯一的选择是手动输入我的收入（这有点烦人，因为我需要我的薪水存根来仔细检查我的收入 - 自家工资）。</p><h2>预算应用程序我们还测试了</h2><h2>亚纳布</h2><p><core-commerce id="827b3d1854364b8fbd1c17dbca4adf40" data-type="product-list" data-original-url="https://www.ynab.com/"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy55bmFiLmNvbS8iLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImRkMTI4MmMzLTk5ZWQtNGRkYy1iOGFiLWMxMGM2MGQ0ZTcwYyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAeIwOwJlNtCMByy-KDHDBAH4fpXBF2OYQeOOanv7gDlW&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ynab.com%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.ynab.com/">YNAB</a> <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy55bmFiLmNvbS93aHkteW5hYi1pcy1kaWZmZXJlbnQiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImRkMTI4MmMzLTk5ZWQtNGRkYy1iOGFiLWMxMGM2MGQ0ZTcwYyJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAbzculKGJPZyG81YhAwbovSAICEEhuKVuaxLxWOnLSKK&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ynab.com%2Fwhy-ynab-is-different" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.ynab.com/why-ynab-is-different">本身</a>是“与您以前尝试过的任何事物不同”。该应用程序的名称缩短了您需要预算，它促进了一个所谓的零预算系统，这迫使您为每笔收入的每一美元分配一个目的。经常使用的类比是将每一美元放在一个信封中。您随时可以将钱从一个信封中移动到另一个信封。这些信封可以包括租金和公用事业，以及不可预见的费用，例如节日礼物和不可避免的汽车维修。这个想法是，如果您每个月为未知数预算一定的费用，他们不会觉得自己正在偷偷摸摸。</p><p>重要的是，YNAB仅关心您现在帐户中的钱。该应用程序不要求您提供带回家的收入或设置经常收入的收入付款（尽管有一种方法可以这样做）。您将在本月晚些时候通过薪水工作赚钱的钱无关紧要，因为YNAB不进行预测。</p><p>该应用程序比这里的任何一个都难以学习，并且需要从用户那里进行更多的努力。 YNAB知道这一点。移动应用程序和Web应用程序内部都是视频和其他教程的链接。尽管我从来没有对用户界面感到满意，但我确实欣赏了YNAB坚持意图的坚持。强迫用户每月起草新的预算并审查每笔交易并不一定是一件坏事。正如YNAB在其网站上所说的那样：“当然，您有饼图表明您在餐馆里花了很多钱，但是您仍然在餐馆里花了大量的钱。”我可以看到，这种方法对于在给定时间不倾向于保留很多现金的人有用，或者他们想要纠正的花费习惯（以YNAB自己的例子进行复兴，订购了无缝的四倍a星期）。</p><p>我的同事瓦伦蒂娜·帕拉迪诺（Valentina Palladino）知道我正在研究这本指南， <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/what-we-bought-how-ynab-gives-me-peace-of-mind-and-keeps-my-money-in-check-140049410.html">并写了一个尊重的反驳</a>，解释了为什么她多年来一直在使用YNAB。也许像她一样，无论是为婚礼付费还是购买房屋，您都有要实现的重大储蓄目标。我建议您阅读她的专栏。但是，对我来说，YNAB的方法感觉就像过度杀伤。</p><h2>袖珍卫士</h2><p><core-commerce id="c0327ccec17449adad76125f040aadd4" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:17;pos:1" href="https://pocketguard.com/">PocketGuard</a>是我在研究中发现的唯一知名的免费预算跟踪器之一。只是知道，自由层的限制要比Nerdwallet或Mint更具限制。在我的测试中，我试图链接两个以上的银行帐户后，提示我要付款。这么多免费，除非您使用一个现金帐户和一张信用卡保持简单。当需要升级到PocketGuard Plus时，您有三个选择：每月支付$ 7.99，每年$ 34.99或一次性终身许可证79.99美元。这种一生的选择实际上是我少数几个独特的卖点之一：我敢肯定，有些人会喜欢付款一次，而不必再付款，呃，再次为此预算。</p><p>从主屏幕上，您可以看到帐户，见解，交易和“计划”的选项卡，这是您看到重复付款在看起来像预算之上的重复付款的地方。主要的概述屏幕向您显示了您的净资产，总资产和债务；净收入和当月的总支出；即将到来的账单；方便提醒您的下一个薪水何时降落；您拥有的任何债务收益计划；和任何目标。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/d31c4260-9dda-11ee-afb4-6c4008638e43" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/d31c4260-9dda-11ee-afb4-6c4008638e43" style="height:1482px;width:1512px;" alt="的屏幕截图" data-uuid="c076978a-47f7-3fa0-8ff0-66f3e112e8d5"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">达纳沃尔曼/Engadget</div></figure><p>像其他一些应用程序一样，包括Quicken Simplifi，PocketGuard也会促进“账单后”方法，您输入所有经常出现的账单，然后PocketGueard向您展示剩下的东西，<em>这就是</em>您应该预算的内容：可支配的收入。显然，其他应用程序具有不同的理念：考虑到您的所有税后收入，并用它来支付账单，购买您想要的东西，甚至可以节省一点。但是在PocketGuard中，最突出的是“口袋里的”号码。值得一提的是，它可以看到哪些账单即将到来以及您已经支付了哪些账单。</p><p> PocketGuard还<a data-i13n="cpos:18;pos:1" href="https://pocketguard.com/news/pocketguard-roadmap/">公开致力于</a>在2024年初添加一些流行的功能。这些功能包括2024年1月的翻转预算，2月份的分类规则和3月共享的家庭访问。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/f23fc180-9dda-11ee-b7ee-4d46dac65aae" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/f23fc180-9dda-11ee-b7ee-4d46dac65aae" style="height:1482px;width:1512px;" alt="PocketGuard 的 iOS 应用程序的屏幕截图。" data-uuid="f81efeff-f753-393c-b645-08623297b62b"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">达纳沃尔曼/Engadget</div></figure><p>尽管PocketGuard的UI很容易理解，但缺乏抛光剂。 “帐户”选项卡有点忙，并且不会显示现金或投资等类别的总数。看似很小的细节，例如奇怪的措辞或标点副本，偶尔会使应用程序感到笨拙。不止一次，它促使我在没有更新时更新应用程序。同时，Web版本感觉就像移动应用程序爆炸成更大的格式，并且无法利用额外的屏幕房地产。</p><p>值得注意的是，尽管PocketGuard确实与Plaid合作，但其主要的银行连接平台实际上是精致的。通过精致设置我的帐户主要是一个简单的过程。我确实遇到了一个打ic：精确度不会连接到我的Sofi帐户。我能够通过格子做到这一点，但是PocketGuard并不容易访问应用程序中的格子。据我所知，唯一的方法是故意搜索无法通过精致的银行的名称，此时您可以选择尝试使用格子。就像我说的那样：经历可能很笨拙。</p><h2>什么是格子，它如何工作？ </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-12/771314a0-9dd8-11ee-bfd6-843fb91c197b"><figcaption></figcaption></figure><p>我测试过的每个应用程序都使用同一基础网络（称为格子）来吸收财务数据，因此值得在自己的部分中解释它的本质和工作方式。 Plaid于2013年成立为金融科技初创公司，如今已成为将银行与第三方应用程序联系起来的行业标准。格子与美国，加拿大和欧洲的12,000多家金融机构合作。<a data-i13n="cpos:19;pos:1" href="https://plaid.com/company/">该公司声称</a>，此外，有8,000多个第三方应用程序和服务依赖格子。</p><p>需要明确的是，您不需要专用的格子应用即可使用它；该技术被烘烤到各种应用程序中，包括我为本指南测试的预算跟踪器。在您使用的哪个中找到“添加帐户”选项后，您将看到常用银行的菜单。您还可以使用一个搜索字段直接查找您的。一旦找到自己的，您将提示您输入登录凭据。如果您设置了两因素身份验证，则还需要输入一次性密码。</p><p>作为中间人，格子是一个可能包括您的帐户余额，交易历史记录，帐户类型和路由或帐号的信息。 Plaid使用加密，并说它具有不向其他公司出售或租用客户数据的政策。但是，如果我没有注意到2022年的<a data-i13n="cpos:20;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/plaid-must-pay-58-million-to-users-of-venmo-robinhood-and-other-apps-085908511.html">格子被迫向消费者支付集体诉讼诉讼的消费者，</a>以收集“比需要更多的财务数据”，我就不会做我的工作。作为和解的一部分，格子被迫改变其某些业务惯例。</p><p>格子发言人在向Engadget提供的一份声明中说，该公司继续否认诉讼的指控，“和解中非金融条款的症结在于，定居点的症结是为了加速美国已经在加速了与使人们更多地透明地进入人们进入的工作流程。格子在连接其帐户中的作用，并确保我们围绕数据最小化的工作流保持正轨。”</p><h2>我的顶级薄荷替代选择：Quicken Simplifi和Copilot Money</h2><p>总而言之，您可能想知道在完成所有这些研究之后我为自己决定了哪个应用程序。答案实际上是两个应用程序：Quicken Simplifi（我的首选）和 Copilot Money。目前，我正在积极使用这两个应用程序，并且仍在决定，从长远来看，我感觉更舒服。我倾向于喜欢 Copilot 快速、丰富多彩的用户界面，但正如我上面所解释的，它太缺乏赌注功能，以至于我无法将其称为最佳整体选择。</p>本文最初出现在https://www.engadget.com/the-best-budgeting-apps-to-replace-mint-143047346.html?src=rss]>;]>;]>;]>;]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-best-budgeting-apps-to-replace-mint-143047346.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> DD1282C3-99ED-4DDC-B8AB-C10C60D4E70C </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Dana Wollman]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 22 Dec 2023 14:30:47 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1706114769</ingested><modified> 2024-01-24T16：46：28+00：00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Personal Investing Ideas & Strategies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mobile Apps]]></category><category><![CDATA[Personal Budgeting]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Banking & Budgeting]]></category><category><![CDATA[Finance]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Dana Wollman]]></category><media:content height="848" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2Fc4b6b150-9ddb-11ee-a7fb-e2be70ffa459&amp;resize=1400%2C848&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=110aee8079ff635d30273ea8b367a008c86c68ab" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="848" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-12%2Fc4b6b150-9ddb-11ee-a7fb-e2be70ffa459&amp;resize=1400%2C848&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=8cf5667edeebad00d21a9fd9342a86e8cabdab02" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Getty]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[An illustration of a smartphone and two people against an orange background meant to convey the idea of a budgeting app]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Budget app]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Mac turns 40: How Apple Silicon cured its midlife crisis]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Mac以前是麦金托什（Macintosh）越严重的麦金托什（Macintosh）今天满40岁，将苹果运行时间最长的产品正处于中年。但是，就像一个看到他们一生的后半部分接近并处于马拉松跑步的形状的人一样，MAC是数十年来最强的地方。从收入的角度来看，MAC的销售在2023年急剧下降，但这是在四年增长的高跟鞋上，这可能是对MAC阵容改善的需求的产物。 </p><div id="a9a49c8a9ea24e18992a7f47d94ef7cc"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/ErwS24cBZPc?si=Wi8f-fOjD81Fg2Vj" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><p> 2020年，苹果终于开始实现这一目标，这在很大程度上要归功于Apple Silicon到达Mac，并迎来了我们现在所处的时代。虽然Mac在Apple Silicon之前处于摇晃的地面上，但现在建议Mac不会到50岁生日会很愚蠢。不过，这并不总是给定的。虽然Mac是苹果最古老的产品，但它也经历了许多时刻，似乎处于无关紧要或完全灾难的边缘。在90年代的大部分时间里，在首席执行官史蒂夫·乔布斯（Steve Jobs）返回领导他创立的公司之前，Macintosh真是一团糟。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>它的功率太昂贵了，苹果的产品阵容令人困惑且混乱，Windows PC现在具有GUI和性能，使Mac成为大多数人的糟糕选择。即使在工作返回并引入了iMac和iBook的同时，在大多数任务中，G3和G4仍然落后于PC。具有讽刺意味的是，即使在十年后将苹果拖延了，2006年向英特尔搬到英特尔，这使Mac更具相关性，因为该公司以“创新”方式追逐了薄且轻便的笔记本电脑设计，例如Touch Bar和Butterfly键盘将其固定在同时。让它的力量陷入困境。 </p><div id="f1723cc601d446b8b01d3c37801b3bc0"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/JcHQXMAd0c0?si=pNNO_jRUmgaBibbD" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><p>但是在2014年，当Mac 30岁时，它处于一个不错的位置。苹果近年来一直专注于iPhone，然后是iPad，前首席执行官史蒂夫·乔布斯（Steve Jobs） <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://allthingsd.com/20130109/steve-jobs-was-right-tablets-are-cars-pcs-are-trucks/"><ins>著名地将PC与卡车进行了比较</ins></a>，这意味着iPad对大多数人来说将是更主流的汽车。但是至少就笔记本电脑而言，Mac相当引人注目。 MacBook Air终于成为乔布斯（Jobs）在2008年将其从舞台上的信封中拉出时所想要的。这是一台薄，轻巧且功能合理的笔记本电脑，价格合理，而人们购买iPod的人的溢出效果则是iPhone帮助MacBook Air在咖啡店和大学校园中变得无处不在。同时，MacBook Pro非常适合创意专业的苹果，屏幕上有很棒的屏幕，足够的端口和足够的功能，可以成为一个引人注目的移动工作室。</p><p>但是，如果您仔细观察，阵容中有很多弱点。也许最明显的是Mac Pro的奇怪传奇。多年来，苹果的塔式计算机变得越来越昂贵，在大多数消费者的范围内都有价格。这本身并不是一件坏事，但是苹果公​​司在2013年发布了圆柱Mac Pro重新设计时未能意识到其目标市场在寻找什么，然后未能有意义地将其升级多年。在缺乏更新和限制可扩展性的设计之间，Mac Pro在十年的大部分时间里在Apple的阵容中有点开玩笑。 </p><div id="290de03a98004d1bbbb5ca1f2da1ab64"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/yjRnEp3kCRc?si=O2TS_hgHV7xuVslw" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><p>然后，苹果在2016年对MacBook Pro进行了类似的灾难性变化。让我们计算苹果公司用这一代笔记本电脑丢下球的方式。首先，似乎存在的<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:2;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-04-23-apple-macbook-keyboard-next-day-repairs-in-store.html" data-original-link="https://www.engadget.com/2019-04-23-apple-macbook-keyboard-next-day-repairs-in-store.html">不可靠的蝴蝶键盘</a>只有苹果可以使这些笔记本电脑尽可能薄和轻。然后删除了HDMI，USB-A和SD卡插槽等有用的端口，仅支持四个USB-C / Thunderbolt端口，其中一个需要充电。还有触摸栏，键盘上的一条薄的OLED条，取决于您使用的应用程序。一个整洁的想法，尽管一个想法未能吸引开发人员或最终用户，并且在未来几年中缺乏物理逃生密钥的用户。</p><p>最后，尽管苹果公司设法使13英寸和15英寸的MacBook Pro模型比其前任更薄，更轻，但它<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2018/07/we-tested-throttling-on-the-macbook-pro-now-apple-says-it-has-a-firmware-fix/"><ins>以性能成本获得了</ins></a>。许多用户经历了过热和CPU节流，好像非常薄的外壳与强大的芯片相结合是一个不好的组合。</p><p>同时，尊贵的MacBook Air被少年的更新和设计和低分辨率的屏幕持续了多年。 iMac和Mac Mini作为寻找台式机的用户的可靠选择，但是当时选择Mac笔记本电脑是妥协的练习，并为可能没有检查所有盒子的东西付费。</p><p>事情显示出在2019年转身的迹象，当时苹果推出了一种新的塔式Mac Pro，并增加了扩展选择。但更重要的是，Apple在可怕的蝴蝶键盘上扭转了课程，并将剪刀风格的钥匙带回了MacBook Pro，几个月后，MacBook Air（此后已使用视网膜显示器和更多的Intel处理器进行了更新）。令人惊讶的是，苹果公司使<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:4;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-11-21-macbook-pro-16-inch-review-ultimate-apple-laptop.html" data-original-link="https://www.engadget.com/2019-11-21-macbook-pro-16-inch-review-ultimate-apple-laptop.html">经过改建的16英寸MacBook Pro</a>比更换的Macbook Pro更重，更重，这表明该公司不惜一切代价从稀薄和更轻的地方移开，尤其是在这样的产品中，这根本没有任何意义以牺牲性能为代价追逐较小的形状。</p><p>但是，当苹果公司发布了公司自定义硅上的第一批Mac时，Mac确实在2020年底反弹。苹果已经设计了芯片多年了，自A4首次到达iPhone 4和2010年的原始iPad以来，该公司所产生的效率和权力组合已被证明是该公司的巨大优势。运行Apple Silicon的第一轮Macs包括Apple最受欢迎的型号，例如MacBook Air和13英寸MacBook Pro。 </p><div id="eb3d2154f8174cd3a75af8867dd5a44a"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/mU0KvHvsiZA?si=ni8kVbOAlJmZ4dfU" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><p>这些改进立即很明显 - <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-macbook-air-m1-review-140031323.html"><ins>当我们审查它时</ins></a>，我们说M1驱动的MacBook Air“重新定义了超实用的可能是什么。”巨大的性能与令人印象深刻的电池寿命相同的组合使MacBook Air毫不费力。同时，如果您正在寻找廉价的台式计算机，MAC MINI就会提供大量的费用。</p><p> Mac的下一个重大举措是在2021年底，当时苹果<a data-i13n="elm:context_link;elmt:doNotAffiliate;cpos:6;pos:1" class="no-affiliate-link" href="https://www.engadget.com/mac-book-pro-14-16-inch-review-2021-apple-mighty-macs-130011975.html" data-original-link="https://www.engadget.com/mac-book-pro-14-16-inch-review-2021-apple-mighty-macs-130011975.html">完全修复了2016年车型引入的MacBook Pro问题</a>。完全重新设计的14英寸和16英寸MacBook Pro模型带回了Apple最初删除，放逐触摸栏并利用新的M1 Pro和M1 Max芯片的许多端口，这些端口促进了这些笔记本电脑的多核能性能，远远超出了其Intel-基于的前辈。</p><p>当苹果推出Mac Studio时，该难题的最后一个主要部分出现在2022年3月。当Mac Pro与Intel Chips徘徊时，新的MAC工作室代表了Pro和Mini之间的中间立场。 2,000美元的型号包括M1 Max Chip，如果您愿意将现金小马，那么您也可以在MacBook Pro中获得，但是4,000美元的型号基本上将其中两个芯片绑在一起以制造M1 Ultra。该Monster处理器具有高达64个GPU核心，而更换它的M2 Ultra可以使您达到76核GPU以及其24核CPU和32核神经发动机，用于机器学习任务。简单而简单，这是Apple很长时间以来没有提供的能力。 </p><div id="84693fdf4d7841f180a29a86bf287e33"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/JRdS1WA2Jy8?si=xA3OH1oO5KeBT14z" title="YouTube 视频播放器" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><p>自 2022 年以来，苹果基本上处于完善、升级和迭代模式，许多 Mac 转向了 M3 架构。但有一些地方仍然需要大修——Mac Pro 在向这些新芯片过渡的后期才转向 Apple Silicon，直到今年 6 月才上市。虽然它有一个可扩展的塔式机箱，但它运行的 M2 Ultra 与 Mac Studio 相同，但价格要高出 3,000 美元。苹果公司可以放入一个甚至高端的工作站级别的机会 - 也许它可以将M3 Ultras中的两个肯定会融合在一起，以进一步将Mac Pro与工作室分开。</p><p>从更加以消费者为中心的水平上，苹果最近在使Mac游戏成为事物方面再次刺伤，该公司将诸如<em>Death Stranding</em>和<em>Resident Evil 4</em>之类的流行，主流游戏带到了平台。但是，尽管Apple Silicon提供了巨大的功率，但该公司仍然没有在Windows上的游戏领域。如果该公司可以找到一种使移植游戏更容易的方法，那么开发人员可能会有一个全新的市场可供出售 - 苹果公司的上限将有另一个羽毛。如果该公司有任何真正推动iPad统治平板电脑市场的方式真正推动PC的野心，那么他们将需要更加努力地推动Mac上的大型游戏。</p><p>而且，当然，我们距离苹果在近十年内发布其第一个新平台仅一周了，Vision Pro。虽然它是一种非常昂贵的独立设备，但不难想象市场是否会逐渐扩大。如果发生这种情况，我们可能会看到一款本地运行 Mac 应用程序的 Vision 设备，而不仅仅是查看它们。不过，苹果长期以来一直坚信自己的平台应该独立——看看对触摸屏 Mac 或 iPad Pro 的 MacOS 版本的徒劳呼吁吧。但是在这种情况下，也许我们将在10年后谈论空间计算是如何向前推动Mac向前发展的。</p>本文最初发表在Engadget上，网址为https://www.engadget.com/the-mac-turns-40-how-apple-silicon-cured-cure--cure--is-midlife-crisis-crisis-crisis-crisis-crisis-crisis-crisis-crisis-crisis-crisis-crisis-crisis-crisis-crisis-crisis-crisis一下， </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-mac-turns-40-how-apple-silicon-cured-its-midlife-crisis-161520642.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 16BD6286-0A57-4363-BEB4-8D90DB4985CF </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathan Ingraham]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 24 Jan 2024 16:15:20 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1706111727</ingested><modified> 2024-01-24T15：55：39+00：00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Computing]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Nathan Ingraham]]></category><media:content height="896" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2021-05%2Ff4fdb100-b752-11eb-ab79-10956a28523a&amp;resize=1400%2C896&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=cd28da25949b42adb7479634de40ab6b4745b47f" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="896" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2021-05%2Ff4fdb100-b752-11eb-ab79-10956a28523a&amp;resize=1400%2C896&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=bbc4729e850ee0c1816347272f938e07fac0750e" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Devindra Hardawar/Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Apple iMac M1 24-inch]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Apple iMac M1 24-inch]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Audio-Technica ATH-TWX7 review: Good earbuds with frustrating flaws]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>我已经期待了音频耳塞和耳机的某些事情。首先，有公司的温暖，舒缓的声音配置文件，一次很容易听。它通常很好，但不一定<em>很好</em>，尽管由于功能和性能，该公司通常将其与可靠的整体体验结合在一起。这一切都在<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/audio-technica-ath-twx7-hands-on-great-audio-compact-design-and-a-call-quality-test-170006493.html"><ins>ATH-TWX7</ins></a>上是正确的：一套<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:B&amp;H Photo;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=95276f3c-7b79-4c1e-803f-981cd9f7a968&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=B%26H+Photo&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATHhxTv5CEZxYAnD0egHQGQQwePK5QPnIRxC4FQxWz2N&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhphotovideo.com%2Fc%2Fproduct%2F1802591-REG%2Faudio_technica_consumer_ath_twx7_noise_canceling_true_wireless_in_ear.html" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.bhphotovideo.com/c/product/1802591-REG/audio_technica_consumer_ath_twx7_noise_canceling_true_wireless_in_ear.html"><ins>199美元</ins></a>的无线耳塞，具有主动噪音消除（ANC）和许多便捷的工具，这些工具与昂贵的竞争对手媲美。有些人比其他工作更好，但是多年来，该公司在扩大其功能方面做得很好，即使ATH-TWX7缺少一个基本项目。</p><h2>设计</h2><p>尽管它们的外观粘长，但ATH-TWX7看起来比大多数类似价格的耳塞更精致。 Audio-Technica选择了黑色和银色（或白色/银色或灰色/银色）的混合物，使耳塞看起来与高端耳机相似。主要住房很小，这转化为我耳朵更舒适的贴合性。该箱子还具有独特的泪珠形状，可以使耳塞坐在一定角度，而不是站立或在充电时完全放平。这里没有真正的好处，但这与值得指出的规范背道而驰。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p><core-commerce id="0439543e18254397a1f97523a025b984" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p> Audio-Technica为ATH-TWX7上的车载控件做了一些事情，在耳塞中很少见。它使用触摸和物理按钮进行播放，呼叫，声音模式并召唤语音助手。 Typically you see this on headphones where the playback controls are touch and the noise cancellation and transparency modes are assigned to a button, but I don&#39;t recall seeing both on earbuds like this before. Granted, I&#39;ve been reviewing audio gear for several years at this point, so I hesitate to proclaim Audio-Technica as the “first” to do so.</p><p> To help you find the ideal fit, Audio-Technica includes two different types of ear tips. One is labeled “soft,” and it&#39;s designed to be more comfortable, while the standard option is meant to offer a more secure fit. I expected the “soft” version to be foam, or at least partially foam, but they&#39;re almost identical. One is slightly thinner, but they both seem to be the same silicone material you see in most earbuds, and neither really feels softer than the other.</p><p> The last thing I&#39;ll point out in terms of the ATH-TWX7&#39;s design is its ingress protection (IP) rating. These are only rated IPX4 against water splashes and they&#39;re not built to withstand spray jets or submersion. That&#39;s probably enough for workouts, and while it&#39;s about average for mid-range earbuds, slightly more expensive models venture into IPX7 territory.</p><h2> Software and features </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2024-01/9079f330-bacc-11ee-b2e4-c2d9c447359b" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2024-01/9079f330-bacc-11ee-b2e4-c2d9c447359b" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="Audio-Technica app" data-uuid="fcd2ec03-1c93-35f5-aeee-2a2939942588"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Billy Steele/Engadget</div></figure><p> When I reviewed the <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-12-20-audio-technica-ath-cks5tw-true-wireless-earbuds-review.html"><ins>ATH-CKS5TW</ins></a> earbuds in late 2019, Audio-Technica&#39;s app was so limited there was really no reason to ever fire it up. Unless it was to install a firmware update, it didn&#39;t offer anything useful and even the onboard control customization was restricted. I&#39;m happy to report that&#39;s no longer the case as the AT Connect software now offers a much more robust list of settings and reconfigurable tools than before.</p><p> The app&#39;s home screen is devoted to options for changing the music codec, EQ and sound mode, as well as showing the battery life for each earbud. Tapping the image of the ATH-TWX7 takes you into the detailed settings, divided into Audio and System sections. All of this is standard fare with access to everything the onboard controls offer in the app, including the ability to remap the touch and physical buttons as you wish. But despite letting you set an automatic power off timer when there&#39;s no audio, the ATH-TWX7 doesn&#39;t have automatic pausing when you take them out of your ears. That&#39;s a big omission in 2024 when almost every set of wireless earbuds does this.</p><p> I will point out a couple of things that are pretty novel. First, under the Call Microphone settings, Audio-Technica goes a step further with an in-app call test so you can hear what you&#39;ll sound like before you dial. This is in addition to features like Natural Mode for quiet locations or Noise-Reduction Mode for windy or loud environments. The latter isn&#39;t very original, but will still come in handy. You can disable the touch controls and just rely on the tiny physical buttons on the earbuds. What is a bit innovative is the ability to tweak the sensitivity of those panels, set to medium by default with low and high options if you need &#39;em.</p><p> The inclusion of both touch and physical buttons gives you <em>a lot</em> of flexibility in terms of how you set those up. Everything on the ATH-TWX7 is reconfigurable, which means you can move things from the buttons to the touch panels and vice versa, or add things that aren&#39;t there by default. In addition to options for playback, calls, voice assistant and noise cancellation settings, you can add Talk-Through, Low Latency Mode and Check Battery Level. Audio-Technica didn&#39;t reinvent the wheel in terms of what these earbuds can do, but the greater customization gives you way more options for assigning tasks in a way that makes the most sense for you.</p><h2> Sound quality and noise cancellation </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2024-01/0d2c0460-bacb-11ee-8dff-8f2f0b180ae7" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2024-01/0d2c0460-bacb-11ee-8dff-8f2f0b180ae7" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="There’s plenty to like about the ATH-TWX7, including a robust set of features that brings a lot of convenience to your day. It offers  solid sound quality and ANC, though a few of those tools could still use some fine-tuning." data-uuid="011c2da5-ff70-3d34-9a31-373fe1416deb"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Billy Steele/Engadget</div></figure><p> Nearly every set of Audio-Technica earbuds and headphones I&#39;ve ever tested has a similar sound profile. It&#39;s a warm, inviting tone that&#39;s pleasant to listen to for hours on end, mostly because the dynamics aren&#39;t exhausting. The ATH-TWX7 is more of the same, for better or worse, with some exceptions.</p><p> Softer, acoustic-driven styles are excellent, with crisp details in drums and guitars that lend texture to tracks like Zach Bryan&#39;s “Heavy Eyes” and Charles Wesley Godwin&#39;s “Family Ties.” The ATH-TWX7 also does well with jazz and synth-heavy pop, rock and instrumental tunes. Hip-hop is nice as well, but the earbuds start to struggle with hard rock, metal and more chaotic, bombastic genres. Better Lovers&#39; “30 Under 13” is still the gritty, raucous hardcore I know and love, but everything sounds flat and has less energy than on other earbuds. The sound on this album and other metal selections like Gojira&#39;s <em>Fortitude</em> is more compressed than with other genres, with less space for everything to open up – especially guitars that typically soar around in your head.</p><p> Like a lot of ANC earbuds, the active noise cancellation on the ATH-TWX7 does well with constant noise, but struggles with things like human voices. This model had no trouble combatting the roar of the noisy heating unit in my Las Vegas hotel during CES, and the same goes for white noise machines and fans at home. It&#39;s not Bose-level sound blocking, but it&#39;s definitely above average.</p><p> Sound quality in Hear-Through or transparency mode is also quite good. There&#39;s a nice, natural element to it that doesn&#39;t seem as compressed or muted as some of the competition. However, the ATH-TWX7 doesn&#39;t pipe in your voice like the AirPods Pro, so the overall effect isn&#39;t as if you aren&#39;t wearing earbuds at all. I assumed the Talk-Through feature would assist with this, but instead that tool simply lowers the volume or mutes content. Confusingly, despite offering two options to let in your surrounding sound, this tool doesn&#39;t let you simply pause. It&#39;s Hear-Through adjacent rather than a truly helpful setting for a quick chat. Because your voice isn&#39;t beamed back to your ears, you&#39;ll still feel the need to speak up, which means you&#39;re more likely to get shouty if you aren&#39;t careful.</p><h2>通话质量</h2><p>Props to Audio-Technica for the easiest way to check call performance ever on the ATH-TWX7. Thanks to that in-app call test, you can get an idea of how you&#39;ll sound before answering or dialing in, which is way better than hoping you sound okay to your caller. I also found this helpful in assessing which setting worked best for where I was at the time, even if I was at home.</p><p> Noise-Reduction Mode lives up to its name, but it also sacrifices some voice quality. Natural mode sounds the best, but it picks up background noise easily. If you&#39;re in a quiet spot though, the ATH-TWX7 gives you above-average voice performance that&#39;s noticeably clearer than the typical speakerphone-like quality most earbuds offer.</p><p> The ATH-TWX7 also seems to struggle a bit with automatic switching via multipoint Bluetooth, but only when it comes to calls. If I was hopping from my phone to my laptop for music or some other audio, the changeover was quick and seamless. However, if I was listening to something on my MacBook Pro and got a call, there were a few times the earbuds had trouble swapping over to it. Since this is the most likely scenario in which I&#39;d need that auto switching, this was disappointing. Best case scenario was for me to tap to change the audio from my iPhone to the ATH-TWX7 after answering, but that&#39;s not really an ideal workflow.</p><h2>电池寿命</h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2024-01/0d2c0460-bacb-11ee-b7df-bdfc920530b3" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2024-01/0d2c0460-bacb-11ee-b7df-bdfc920530b3" style="height:1333px;width:2000px;" alt="There’s plenty to like about the ATH-TWX7, including a robust set of features that brings a lot of convenience to your day. It offers  solid sound quality and ANC, though a few of those tools could still use some fine-tuning." data-uuid="e9339a03-2195-36e5-b254-0b380e2aa717"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Billy Steele/Engadget</div></figure><p> Audio-Technica promised up to 6.5 hours on the earbuds themselves with two additional charges in the case. It doesn&#39;t specify if that&#39;s with ANC on or off, but during my tests I had no trouble hitting the stated figure while blocking background noise. That&#39;s doing a mix of music and calls, with the occasional few minutes of Hear-Through mode and leaving the ATH-TWX7 to automatically turn off twice. I could reliably eke out 30 minutes more than the company claimed, and a few minutes extra is always a good thing.</p><h2>比赛</h2><p>In the $200 price range, an apt comparison for the ATH-TWX7 are <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sony-linkbuds-s-announced-specs-price-160028671.html"><ins>Sony&#39;s LinkBuds S</ins></a> . An honorable mention on our <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-wireless-earbuds-120058222.html"><ins>best wireless earbuds</ins></a> list, these have similar battery life and the same IPX4 rating, but are more comfortable to wear and have some trademark Sony features. Those include support for DSEE Extreme upscaling in addition to Quick Attention Mode that&#39;s handy for quick chats in the office, coffee shop or airport. What&#39;s more, the LinkBuds S can automatically pause when you speak and an adaptive sound mode can be configured to change settings based on activity or location. Plus, they&#39;re available for $200 at full price.</p><p> iPhone owners will be more satisfied with <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/airpods-pro-review-second-generation-130048218.html"><ins>the second-gen AirPods Pro</ins></a> over the ATH-TWX7. Currently available for under $200, the 2022 version of the earbuds are the best option if your life is intertwined with iOS, iPadOS and macOS. New features like Adaptive Audio bring automatic adjustments to your day and Apple&#39;s take on transparency mode continues to be the best in the business. Lastly, they&#39;re more comfortable for a longer period of time than the ATH-TWX7.</p><h2>包起来</h2><p>There&#39;s plenty to like about the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:B&amp;H Photo;elmt:;cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=95276f3c-7b79-4c1e-803f-981cd9f7a968&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=B%26H+Photo&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAATHhxTv5CEZxYAnD0egHQGQQwePK5QPnIRxC4FQxWz2N&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhphotovideo.com%2Fc%2Fproduct%2F1802591-REG%2Faudio_technica_consumer_ath_twx7_noise_canceling_true_wireless_in_ear.html" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.bhphotovideo.com/c/product/1802591-REG/audio_technica_consumer_ath_twx7_noise_canceling_true_wireless_in_ear.html"><ins>ATH-TWX7</ins></a> . A robust set of features brings a lot of convenience to your day. But a few of those tools could still use some fine-tuning and the lack of automatic pausing in 2024 is a head scratcher. Still, the audio is mostly good, albeit inconsistent at times, and transparency mode is better than most. Add in the solid call quality and the in-app voice test and the ATH-TWX7 are a worthy consideration, especially at this price. Too bad it falls short of being a more complete package some of the competition offers for a slightly larger investment.</p><core-slideshow data-slideshowid="91aadda2-dcb9-4b51-8559-991d6ac7f4cb" /><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/audio-technica-ath-twx7-review-good-earbuds-with-frustrating-flaws-160054450.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/audio-technica-ath-twx7-review-good-earbuds-with-frustrating-flaws-160054450.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> c3df5bfd-8884-4fd3-bc86-c0f4c4643ac8 </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Billy Steele]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 24 Jan 2024 16:00:54 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1706111163</ingested><modified> 2024-01-24T15:46:19+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Audio Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Billy Steele]]></category><media:content height="933" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F0d2c0461-bacb-11ee-baf9-8e3df04fd24f&amp;resize=1400%2C933&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=0e9124971d44b71346bfbe6ada1a90bc956f94f2" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="933" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F0d2c0461-bacb-11ee-baf9-8e3df04fd24f&amp;resize=1400%2C933&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=8eed3ce339aaca6dd104d74dc5ef10d18f2a3c35" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Billy Steele/Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[There’s plenty to like about the ATH-TWX7, including a robust set of features that brings a lot of convenience to your day. It offers  solid sound quality and ANC, though a few of those tools could still use some fine-tuning.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Audio-Technica ATH-TWX7 review]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The best gaming headsets for 2024]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Most of the time, the best gaming headset isn&#39;t a “gaming headset” at all. Although these devices are often thought of as a distinct niche within the wider headphone market, they&#39;re ultimately <em>still headphones</em> . And while it&#39;s certainly not impossible to find gaming headsets that sound nice, those tend to cost much more than a comparable pair of wired headphones (yes, those still exist).<br><br> A good wired headphone remains your best bet if you want the most detailed sound possible at any given price point and don&#39;t need something especially portable, which is usually the case while gaming. If you need to chat with friends, you can always buy an external microphone, whether it&#39;s a USB mic, a cheaper <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-mobile-microphones-for-recording-with-a-phone-154536629.html">clip-on model</a> or a standalone option like the <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://antlionaudio.com/collections/microphones/">Antlion ModMic</a> or <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAc3eyz3tAa5ZiXqoOSXXUJbQ9_Y1rClL-8LF-6d_J8BW&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FV-MODA-BoomPro-Microphone-Gaming-Communication%2Fdp%2FB00BJ17WKK%2F">V-Moda BoomPro</a> . Oftentimes, those&#39;ll make your voice sound clearer and fuller than a gaming headset&#39;s built-in mic.<br><br> But we recognize that many people just want the convenience of an all-in-one combo. So after testing out a few dozen pairs over the past several months, we&#39;ve put together a list of good headphones for gaming and full-on gaming headsets. We recommend you consider the former first, but all of them will make your play time more enjoyable.</p><h2> What to look for in good gaming headphones </h2><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-04/7a99ecc0-d95c-11ed-b13c-943d83f982b8" alt="A black gaming headset with a built-in boom microphone, the HyperX Cloud Stinger 2, rests on a white table in an outdoors setting." data-uuid="418ab01d-8853-3a4d-8a2e-10b7ce177a91"><figcaption> The HyperX Cloud Stinger 2.</figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Jeff Dunn / Engadget</div></figure><p> Evaluating headphones is a particularly subjective exercise, so calling one pair the absolute “best” is something of a fool&#39;s errand. At a certain point, whether you&#39;re an audiophile or not, everything becomes a matter of taste. For most, a headphone with a wide soundscape and strong imaging performance — ie, the ability to position sounds correctly, so you can more precisely tell where footsteps and other game effects are coming from — will provide the most immersive gaming experience, the kind that makes you feel like your head is <em>within</em> a given scene.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> For that, you want a high-quality pair of open-back headphones. That is to say, an over-ear pair whose ear cups do not completely seal off the ear from air and outside noise. These are inherently terrible at isolating you from external sound and preventing others from hearing what you&#39;re playing, so if you often play games in a noisy environment, their benefits will be blunted. But in a quiet room, the best open-back pairs sound significantly wider and more precise than more common closed-back models.</p><p> More up for debate is <em>how</em> a good gaming headphone should sound. If you want something that&#39;ll help you in competitive multiplayer games, you may prefer a headphone with a flatter sound signature, which&#39;ll keep a game&#39;s mix from being overly boosted in one direction and is less likely to mask the smaller details of what&#39;s happening around you. A slightly brighter sound, one that pushes the upper frequencies a tad, may also work. Open-back headphones almost never have huge sub-bass, so you rarely have to worry about low-end sounds muddying up the rest of the signature. In this light, the fact that an overwhelming amount of gaming headsets are closed-back and bass-heavy seems counterintuitive.</p><p> Lots of people love bass, though. And if you don&#39;t really care about competitive play, some extra low-end can add a touch of excitement to action scenes or rousing soundtracks. You still don&#39;t want a pair that boosts the low-end too hard — as many gaming headsets do — but the point is that what makes a pair “immersive” to one person may sound dull to another. </p><p><core-commerce id="492a8e7747d84e979413f30261071c8d" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p><core-commerce id="fe20463957704cd4855a0e6658ed6270" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p><core-commerce id="fd9ce75cc4834016bb34789626bb1099" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p><core-commerce id="c990c3baa2b143c2a225d3fd9dced20b" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p><core-commerce id="ff3b0030a2cf43c984a48388b03a114b" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><h2> A quick PSA on wireless gaming headsets</h2><p> Most people do not <em>need</em> a wireless gaming headset. The PS5 and Xbox Series X/S have a headphone jack built into their controllers, while the Nintendo Switch and most gaming PCs still carry the port as well. The cost of an OK wireless headset is often higher than a comparable wired one, and for the money most wireless models tend to provide worse audio quality and less-clear microphones. You also risk introducing issues with latency. (That&#39;s why non-gaming Bluetooth headphones are a no-go here.) That said, the top end of the wireless headset market has improved noticeably in terms of audio, mic and battery performance over the past couple of years. You&#39;ll still have to pay a significant premium to get one of those options, so they aren&#39;t great values — but if you absolutely must go wireless, you won&#39;t have to make as much of a sacrifice as you used to. </p><p><core-commerce id="7af406b256fa49fe94800a5d12f75950" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p><core-commerce id="67dc0cfe95e34927846a82714f0cae16" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><h2>荣誉奖</h2><p><core-commerce id="fcb9cd58e6e34636b29e14364aba19cd" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p><core-commerce id="aa6b54baa4fe4078a5994c3950634a3f" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p><core-commerce id="225a6214d5094994ab0a29c0d980fff4" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><h2> Other gaming headsets we tested</h2><p> If the Audeze Maxwell is out of stock, the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2RwL0IwQjNGOFY0Skc_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tc20tMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImE2ZmE2N2E3LTc2YTgtNGVmMS05YzhkLTU5YzQ2M2NiM2FkYiJ9&amp;signature=AQAAAbpn4rT3AeLvSu8AzET3Iez3ZBIJqXzzTNwOj3DOnxV-&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB0B3F8V4JG" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0B3F8V4JG">Logitech G Pro X 2 Lightspeed</a> is another quality wireless headset worth considering. It sounds better than the HyperX Cloud Alpha Wireless, with satisfying but more controlled bass and more accurate mids, and it&#39;s lighter on the head than the Maxwell. Logitech rates its battery life at 50 hours, but we found it to last much longer at moderate volumes. However, similar to the Astro A50 X, a dip in the treble makes it sound darker and more veiled than the Maxwell, and it doesn&#39;t have any HDMI-switching tricks to fall back on. Its mic also sounds less natural than those of the Maxwell, A50 X and Cloud Alpha Wireless. Plus, while it can connect over a USB dongle, Bluetooth or a 3.5mm cable, it can&#39;t pair to two devices at once like Audeze&#39;s and Astro&#39;s pairs. Our biggest issue is the price: Value-wise, it&#39;s in something of a no man&#39;s land at its MSRP of $250. It&#39;s a fine choice if it dips below $200, though.</p><p> Xbox owners who want a more affordable wireless headset than the Audeze Maxwell could do worse than the <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAbsvlo44Q_b9j-3DMGUI_5ZcSvzTc0o-amxEdFVDnGwy&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSteelSeries-Arctis-Multi-Platform-Gaming-Mobile-Headset%2Fdp%2FB0B8QP5BGD" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/SteelSeries-Arctis-Multi-Platform-Gaming-Mobile-Headset/dp/B0B8QP5BGD">SteelSeries Arctis Nova 7X</a> . It&#39;s another bass-forward pair, and its mic is comparable to that of the Cloud Alpha Wireless. It offers multiple connectivity options, including Bluetooth and a 3.5mm cable. While it&#39;s marketed for Xbox, it can also connect to PCs and PS5s. Its 30-ish-hour battery life is well short of the Maxwell and Cloud Alpha Wireless, however, and its uneven treble can cause things like in-game dialogue to sound masked in certain titles.</p><p> The wired <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9kcC9CMDc0TkJTRjlOP3RhZz1nZGd0MGMtcC1vLXNtLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJhNmZhNjdhNy03NmE4LTRlZjEtOWM4ZC01OWM0NjNjYjNhZGIifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAZBXk5cw9Z-Zz-xHLFBiaCe1h-9KKpmO19dQ6jLR-Z-I&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB074NBSF9N">HyperX Cloud Alpha</a> often goes for $80 or less, and at that price it&#39;s a decent middle ground between the Cloud Stinger 2 and Astro A40 if you really want a closed-back gaming headset. It&#39;s old, but its plush earpads and headband are comfy, and its detachable mic, while not superb, is still better than the one on the A40. Its treble is underemphasized, however, and again it sounds more “in your head” than Astro&#39;s pair. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2024-01/128d3160-bac9-11ee-a9f3-0f77afcdd31a" data-crop-orig-src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2024-01/128d3160-bac9-11ee-a9f3-0f77afcdd31a" style="height:1199px;width:2000px;" alt="The Beyerdynamic MMX 200 and HyperX Cloud III Wireless gaming headsets lay on their sides on top of a brown wooden table." data-uuid="8e148108-1065-3a88-8a35-1728f9d68224"><figcaption> The Beyerdynamic MMX 200 (left) and HyperX Cloud III Wireless (right).</figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Jeff Dunn / Engadget</div></figure><p> The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2dwL3Byb2R1Y3QvQjA5WldGOUJDSj90YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1zbS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTZmYTY3YTctNzZhOC00ZWYxLTljOGQtNTljNDYzY2IzYWRiIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAYmc5HQmnL28E9ZIMdbYY0y6ND3-6B1G9FAW9dN1MutV&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09ZWF9BCJ" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B09ZWF9BCJ">SteelSeries Arctis Nova Pro</a> is comfortable and has a noticeably clearer mic than the Astro A40. It also comes with a useful DAC that makes it easy to adjust the headset&#39;s EQ and game-to-chat mix on the fly. However, its closed-back design can&#39;t provide the same enveloping sense of width, and its default sound can sound piercing in the treble. Like the Virtuoso Pro, it&#39;s also a bit too pricey, typically hovering in the $200 to $220 range.</p><p> The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2dwL3Byb2R1Y3QvQjA5WldDWVFUWD90YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1zbS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTZmYTY3YTctNzZhOC00ZWYxLTljOGQtNTljNDYzY2IzYWRiIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAVKMqgDV_cgGYF8_Qq7ERisWwewwraqoHl_7CfZv25Ew&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB09ZWCYQTX" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B09ZWCYQTX">SteelSeries Arctis Nova Pro Wireless</a> is largely similar to its wired counterpart but adds a passable level of active noise cancellation. Being able to hot-swap battery packs and connect to multiple devices at once is also nice. It&#39;s not <em>as</em> convenient for multi-console play as the Astro A50 X, though, and it usually costs more than the Audeze Maxwell, which sounds better, has a superior mic and lasts longer on a charge.</p><p> The wireless <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2dwL3Byb2R1Y3QvQjBDR1g4TFJTSC9yZWY9b3hfc2NfYWN0X3RpdGxlXzE_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tc20tMjAiLCJjb250ZW50VXVpZCI6ImE2ZmE2N2E3LTc2YTgtNGVmMS05YzhkLTU5YzQ2M2NiM2FkYiJ9&amp;signature=AQAAARkdVIpbTgyJjl1aKjQD7BrHhVoTj9zAwYHkgyN4l-tY&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB0CGX8LRSH%2Fref%3Dox_sc_act_title_1" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0CGX8LRSH/ref=ox_sc_act_title_1?smid=A3GB3YUSIMIV1W&amp;th=1">Beyerdynamic MMX 200</a> locates in-game effects accurately, feels sturdy and has a great boom mic, but it sounds less articulate than the Audeze Maxwell, with heavily exaggerated bass and recessed lower-mids. There&#39;s no game-to-chat mix or custom EQ tools, which is tough for a $250 headset, and its 35-hour battery life is unremarkable. We also found its sweat-inducing ear cushions and headband to clamp down too tight for comfort. However, the built-in transparency mode is nice and the tight fit does a good job of isolating outside noise.</p><p> The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5hbWF6b24uY29tL2dwL3Byb2R1Y3QvQjBDQlFZS0ZSMj90YWc9Z2RndDBjLXAtby1zbS0yMCIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYTZmYTY3YTctNzZhOC00ZWYxLTljOGQtNTljNDYzY2IzYWRiIn0&amp;signature=AQAAATHMcnWIGRc1P7nEbqcI8CTc1SA_kAOW4a1AzOR5Gqmq&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB0CBQYKFR2" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B0CBQYKFR2">HyperX Cloud III Wireless</a> is comfy and can last up to 120 hours per charge but sounds less dynamic than the older Cloud Alpha Wireless, with weaker bass response. Like that pair, it also lacks a 3.5mm jack, Bluetooth audio support and Xbox compatibility. The Cloud Alpha Wireless still gets nearly three times the battery life, too, so it remains a better buy if you want a wireless headset for PC or PS5 in the $150 range.</p><p> The <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Razer;elmt:;cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=d043077a-4ba1-4321-a933-30b8701d8d31&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Razer&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5yYXplci5jb20vZ2FtaW5nLWhlYWRzZXRzL3JhemVyLWJsYWNrc2hhcmstdjIvUlowNC0wMzIzMDEwMC1SM1UxIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJhNmZhNjdhNy03NmE4LTRlZjEtOWM4ZC01OWM0NjNjYjNhZGIifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAXkPurSg94ReSmafzjOxi9X0iZeaCVEQ8qupAHvUVtMN&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.razer.com%2Fgaming-headsets%2Frazer-blackshark-v2%2FRZ04-03230100-R3U1" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.razer.com/gaming-headsets/razer-blackshark-v2/RZ04-03230100-R3U1">Razer BlackShark V2</a> is lightweight and easy to wear, plus it doesn&#39;t sound bad for a $100 closed-back headset. But it&#39;s still not as immersive as the Astro A40, its mic makes voices sound thinner than the HyperX Cloud Alpha, and its plastic design feels cheap.</p><p> The $60 <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Xbox;elmt:;cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=5f41950e-8ca3-4481-8466-a22b28b80e32&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Xbox&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy54Ym94LmNvbS9lbi1VUy9hY2Nlc3Nvcmllcy9oZWFkc2V0cy94Ym94LXN0ZXJlby1oZWFkc2V0IiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJhNmZhNjdhNy03NmE4LTRlZjEtOWM4ZC01OWM0NjNjYjNhZGIifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAel2OwHqP2B7m-UO6Q7C1guhGfdHViGxe5KzXdheh3s0&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.xbox.com%2Fen-US%2Faccessories%2Fheadsets%2Fxbox-stereo-headset" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.xbox.com/en-US/accessories/headsets/xbox-stereo-headset">Xbox Stereo Headset</a> straight up sounds bad, with overblown bass and underemphasized treble that makes finer details feel like they&#39;re underwater.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/best-gaming-headset-130006477.html?src=rss]]>;</description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/best-gaming-headset-130006477.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> a6fa67a7-76a8-4ef1-9c8d-59c463cb3adb </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jeff Dunn]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Fri, 03 Nov 2023 11:55:35 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1706117412</ingested><modified> 2024-01-24T17:30:20+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Personal Finance - Lifestyle]]></category><category><![CDATA[Audio Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jeff Dunn]]></category><media:content height="840" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-04%2Fa05a6150-d967-11ed-bc5f-50bcb25e8639&amp;resize=1400%2C840&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=e4ff8354c27630b0fe73467ec1a099c3fb8788c7" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="840" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2023-04%2Fa05a6150-d967-11ed-bc5f-50bcb25e8639&amp;resize=1400%2C840&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=6f88c6c80ce4d276638a56931315552aef3bf76f" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Jeff Dunn / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Best gaming headsets]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Best gaming headsets]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Nintendo will shut down most Wii U and 3DS online services by April 8]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/nintendo/"><ins>Nintendo</ins></a> has <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://en-americas-support.nintendo.com/app/answers/detail/a_id/63227"><ins>revealed</ins></a> exactly when most remaining online services for the <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/3ds/"><ins>3DS</ins></a> and <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/wii-u/"><ins>Wii U</ins></a> will come to an end. After 7AM ET on April 8, it will no longer be possible to jump into a multiplayer match on the original <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2014-06-12-the-curious-case-of-splatoon-wii-us-dollop-of-squidly-joy.html"><em><ins>Splatoon</ins></em></a> <em>&nbsp;</em> or check out other players&#39; levels in <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nintendo-winds-down-super-mario-maker-wii-u-163008385.html"><em><ins>Super Mario Maker</ins></em></a> . Online co-op play, leaderboards and data distribution are among the features that won&#39;t be available on either console (unless you find an adequate homebrew solution). The Badge Arcade feature, which allows players to customize their Nintendo 3DS home menu, is going away too.</p><p> Nintendo previously said that online services on the systems <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nintendo-will-take-3ds-and-wii-u-services-offline-in-early-april-2024-091001733.html"><ins>would end in early April</ins></a> , but hadn&#39;t shared a specific date until now. It also warned that it may &quot;have to discontinue services earlier than planned&quot; — some players had <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/nintendo-starts-shutting-down-online-play-for-wii-u-and-3ds-months-ahead-of-schedule-191720412.html"><ins>difficulty accessing them late last year</ins></a> . </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><div id="89c1067f85b1482b8c2a281e6433bd67"><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">更新：自 4 月 8 日起，Nintendo 3DS 和 Wii U 软件的在线游戏和其他使用在线通信的功能将终止服务。非常感谢您一直以来对我们产品的支持。<br><br> Find out more: <a href="https://t.co/VdIdewGmB5">https://t.co/VdIdewGmB5</a></p> - 美国任天堂 (@NintendoAmerica) <a href="https://twitter.com/NintendoAmerica/status/1749963072998166670?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2024 年 1 月 24 日</a></blockquote></div><p>Single-player games and modes will continue to work on both platforms. Nintendo said there will be some exceptions to the end of online services and suggests that players of third-party games contact publishers to check whether they&#39;ll keep servers running. The company also notes that Pokémon Bank and Poké Transporter features will remain available for now, and you&#39;ll still be able to download updates and games you&#39;ve previously purchased on either system for the foreseeable future. Nintendo <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/its-your-last-chance-to-buy-from-nintendos-wii-u-and-3ds-eshops-072838697.html"><ins>shut down</ins></a> the eShop on both 3DS and Wii U last March.</p><p> One other feature that will remain is StreetPass on 3DS, since that connects to other 3DS units over local communication. SpotPass will be discontinued, however, as that requires an internet connection.</p><p> Meanwhile, the company <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://en-americas-support.nintendo.com/app/answers/detail/a_id/64132"><ins>says</ins></a> that 3DS and Wii U owners have until 1AM ET on March 12 to <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://en-americas-support.nintendo.com/app/answers/detail/a_id/22369"><ins>merge their Nintendo Network ID and Nintendo Account</ins></a> . If they do, they can spend any unused balance on either system&#39;s eShop on Nintendo Switch games, DLC and other digital content.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/nintendo-will-shut-down-most-wii-u-and-3ds-online-services-by-april-8-150807925.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/nintendo-will-shut-down-most-wii-u-and-3ds-online-services-by-april-8-150807925.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 8b92a89d-c56d-4612-b6ad-f90970d5f8e3 </guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Kris Holt]]></dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder><![CDATA[Engadget]]></dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Wed, 24 Jan 2024 15:08:07 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1706108888</ingested><modified> 2024-01-24T15:08:13+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Game Consoles]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="939" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Fos%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F6a7fb050-bac9-11ee-8bdd-25c4d0cc2ce5&amp;resize=1400%2C939&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=3035d624de094941188e77b82b43388a9a60f3bc" width="1400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="939" medium="image" url="https://o.aolcdn.com/images/dims?image_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fcreatr-uploaded-images%2F2024-01%2F6a7fb050-bac9-11ee-8bdd-25c4d0cc2ce5&amp;resize=1400%2C939&amp;client=19f2b5e49a271b2bde77&amp;signature=322a6d1728421d6f9c14ceeeca8a45479a4950e8" width="1400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[REUTERS / Reuters]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A shopper is seen behind a advertisement board of Nintendo Co Ltd's Wii U game console at an electronics retail store in Tokyo January 29, 2014. Nintendo Co Ltd, facing a third year of losses, is getting lots of unsolicited advice on how to squeeze more out of its Mario franchise and revive its fortunes after admitting that its Wii U game console has been a flop. REUTERS/Yuya Shino (JAPAN - Tags: BUSINESS SCIENCE TECHNOLOGY)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[A shopper is seen behind a advertisement board of Nintendo Co Ltd's Wii U game console at